WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:35.827 --> 00:00:39.915
[birds chirping]

3
00:00:39.998 --> 00:00:44.670
[tense music playing]

4
00:00:58.559 --> 00:01:00.959
[woman in Portuguese] We've gone
as far as we can go by road.

5
00:01:01.228 --> 00:01:02.854
We need a boat.

6
00:01:03.689 --> 00:01:06.400
Should only take a few days.

7
00:01:06.483 --> 00:01:09.111
We shouldn't be here.

8
00:01:09.194 --> 00:01:11.071
The jungle doesn't want us here.

9
00:01:11.154 --> 00:01:13.156
- [rustling]
- There is…

10
00:01:13.699 --> 00:01:15.200
[gasps]

11
00:01:24.126 --> 00:01:27.921
[footsteps on car]

12
00:01:30.465 --> 00:01:33.218
[suspenseful music playing]

13
00:01:37.431 --> 00:01:39.641
- [monkey shrieks]
- [woman exclaims in shock]

14
00:01:41.143 --> 00:01:42.644
[both breathing heavily]

15
00:01:44.855 --> 00:01:46.690
We have to do this.

16
00:01:47.399 --> 00:01:49.735
What's waiting for us
will change our lives.

17
00:01:51.570 --> 00:01:53.447
Eh? Fine.

18
00:01:54.323 --> 00:01:55.490
I'll go alone.

19
00:01:55.574 --> 00:01:56.825
Ana.

20
00:01:56.908 --> 00:01:57.909
[man] Ana!

21
00:01:58.827 --> 00:01:59.828
Don't do this!

22
00:02:03.457 --> 00:02:07.252
[adventurous music playing]

23
00:02:17.429 --> 00:02:18.472
It's her.

24
00:02:18.555 --> 00:02:21.808
[thrilling music playing]

25
00:02:24.686 --> 00:02:26.063
[swears in Portuguese]

26
00:02:26.813 --> 00:02:28.315
[motorcycle starts]

27
00:02:29.107 --> 00:02:30.867
[man 1 shouts in Portuguese]
Get to the boat!

28
00:02:39.034 --> 00:02:40.619
Come on! Let's go!

29
00:02:41.286 --> 00:02:42.537
[screams. groans]

30
00:02:42.621 --> 00:02:44.414
- Hey!
- [man 2 groans] Stop!

31
00:02:44.498 --> 00:02:46.875
Take my hand!

32
00:02:46.958 --> 00:02:52.422
[shouting in Portuguese]

33
00:02:54.800 --> 00:02:56.676
[muffled scream]

34
00:02:56.760 --> 00:03:00.806
[upbeat music playing]

35
00:03:00.889 --> 00:03:03.100
[music fades]

36
00:03:03.183 --> 00:03:05.343
[male voice. in English]
<i>We start tight on a full moon.</i>

37
00:03:06.103 --> 00:03:08.146
<i>Milky. Almost yellow.</i>

38
00:03:09.564 --> 00:03:10.941
<i>And we crane down</i>

39
00:03:11.817 --> 00:03:16.029
<i>to reveal an idyllic. suburban street.</i>

40
00:03:16.947 --> 00:03:20.409
<i>We float past a series
of white picket fences.</i>

41
00:03:20.492 --> 00:03:22.285
<i>until we settle on a sewer grate.</i>

42
00:03:23.453 --> 00:03:24.871
Pow! Flies open!

43
00:03:25.539 --> 00:03:28.291
Something big and scaly slithers out.

44
00:03:28.375 --> 00:03:31.586
fast. hungry. definitely not human.

45
00:03:31.670 --> 00:03:33.672
as a pulsating score kicks in.

46
00:03:34.297 --> 00:03:38.301
[vocalizing score]

47
00:03:38.385 --> 00:03:40.929
[suspenseful music playing]

48
00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:44.933
We're on the back of the beast

49
00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:48.186
as it slithers menacingly
towards a little blue house.

50
00:03:48.270 --> 00:03:51.940
[hissing]

51
00:03:52.023 --> 00:03:56.319
[vocalizing score]

52
00:03:57.612 --> 00:04:00.407
[suspenseful music continues]

53
00:04:01.783 --> 00:04:03.452
- Wait. I'm sorry.
- [music stops]

54
00:04:03.535 --> 00:04:06.121
This is our wedding video
you're talking about?

55
00:04:06.204 --> 00:04:08.665
Yes. though I actually
don't think of them as videos.

56
00:04:08.749 --> 00:04:09.809
They're more like short films.

57
00:04:09.833 --> 00:04:14.379
Yeah. because I'm not sure
this is quite what we had in mind.

58
00:04:14.463 --> 00:04:16.566
Okay. I know.
It's a little different than normal but...

59
00:04:16.590 --> 00:04:19.885
We really liked the one you did
for Karen and Bart.

60
00:04:19.968 --> 00:04:21.404
[exclaims] When they walk by the river

61
00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:23.346
- and jump up and high-five.
- That jump was dope.

62
00:04:23.430 --> 00:04:25.140
And I loved that song they used.

63
00:04:25.223 --> 00:04:29.728
[sings] ♪ <i>I don't want to wait</i>
<i>For our lives to be over </i> ♪

64
00:04:29.811 --> 00:04:33.315
♪ <i>I want to know right now</i>
<i>How does it feel </i> ♪

65
00:04:33.398 --> 00:04:35.984
- [bride] You know it. Yeah.
- Um. guys. Here's the thing.

66
00:04:36.067 --> 00:04:39.154
I really like you guys.
And you said you're horror fans.

67
00:04:39.237 --> 00:04:41.239
and I'm like. "I love horror so much."

68
00:04:41.323 --> 00:04:44.075
And I thought this could be special.
You know what I mean?

69
00:04:44.159 --> 00:04:46.703
This is a film you're gonna watch
for the rest of your lives.

70
00:04:46.787 --> 00:04:48.872
But this isn't a film. Doug.

71
00:04:48.955 --> 00:04:52.667
This is a wedding video. and we want one
where they do a little jump.

72
00:04:52.751 --> 00:04:53.668
- [groom] Yeah.
- [dad] Now. can you do that

73
00:04:53.752 --> 00:04:54.753
for us or not?

74
00:04:57.464 --> 00:05:01.134
[vocal warm-ups]

75
00:05:02.177 --> 00:05:03.512
Okay.

76
00:05:03.595 --> 00:05:06.348
And do you mind if I'm doing warm-ups?
Is it okay?

77
00:05:06.431 --> 00:05:08.642
Oh. yeah. I've… I've seen much crazier.

78
00:05:08.725 --> 00:05:09.893
Okay. good.

79
00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:12.103
Does it sound better to say my line.

80
00:05:12.187 --> 00:05:15.232
"His vision is blurry.
which could suggest."

81
00:05:15.315 --> 00:05:18.443
[tone shifts] or. "His vision
is blurry. which could suggest…"

82
00:05:18.527 --> 00:05:21.297
Or I could… You know what? I could even
do. like. an accent. I could do just…

83
00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:23.962
Oh. I think you just should do it
the way you auditioned it. honey.

84
00:05:24.032 --> 00:05:24.908
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

85
00:05:24.991 --> 00:05:28.995
It's been a while since I booked anything.
and I just want it to go well.

86
00:05:29.079 --> 00:05:30.247
- Yeah.
- I just…

87
00:05:30.330 --> 00:05:31.540
It's hard out there.

88
00:05:32.290 --> 00:05:34.000
[groans] Sorry.

89
00:05:34.084 --> 00:05:35.710
Doctor number 3. we're ready for you.

90
00:05:35.794 --> 00:05:37.104
[makeup artist] Okay. knock 'em dead.

91
00:05:37.128 --> 00:05:38.755
Okay. thanks. Thank you. Donna.

92
00:05:38.838 --> 00:05:41.466
Hey. by the way. if you ever
need anything from Lowe's.

93
00:05:41.550 --> 00:05:43.470
uh. I will hook you up
with my employee discount.

94
00:05:43.510 --> 00:05:44.711
no questions asked. [Chuckles]

95
00:05:45.387 --> 00:05:46.513
- Okay?
- [chuckles] Okay.

96
00:05:46.596 --> 00:05:49.099
[lively music playing]

97
00:05:51.476 --> 00:05:54.104
Thanks. Ten more cc's of tramadol.

98
00:05:54.187 --> 00:05:55.689
Any idea what I'm looking at here?

99
00:05:55.772 --> 00:05:57.333
[in British accent]
He said his vision was blurry.

100
00:05:57.357 --> 00:06:00.860
- so. you know. that could suggest...
- Optic neuritis.

101
00:06:01.444 --> 00:06:02.922
- Already ruled that out.
- [bell ringing]

102
00:06:02.946 --> 00:06:04.340
- [director] Cut.
- [assistant director] That's a cut!

103
00:06:04.364 --> 00:06:06.825
[director] Hey. buddy.
not sure what that accent is.

104
00:06:06.908 --> 00:06:08.368
Just do it normally. okay?

105
00:06:09.160 --> 00:06:11.180
- We're gonna go again right away.
- [assistant director] Set.

106
00:06:11.204 --> 00:06:15.792
[speaking slowly] He said his vision
was blurry. which could suggest...

107
00:06:15.875 --> 00:06:18.920
[director] Cut! Say the line faster. Okay?
Faster this time.

108
00:06:19.004 --> 00:06:21.274
[rushed] He said his vision was blurry.
which could suggest...

109
00:06:21.298 --> 00:06:23.675
Cut! Jesus.
I think we gotta fire this guy.

110
00:06:23.758 --> 00:06:25.635
[director]
Can we get somebody else in here?

111
00:06:26.136 --> 00:06:31.891
["Have You Ever Seen The Rain?"
by Creedence Clearwater Revival playing]

112
00:06:39.232 --> 00:06:42.235
<i>♪ When it's over. so they say ♪</i>

113
00:06:43.320 --> 00:06:46.239
<i>♪ It'll rain a sunny day ♪</i>

114
00:06:46.323 --> 00:06:52.329
<i>♪ I know. shinin' down like water ♪</i>

115
00:06:56.082 --> 00:06:58.543
<i>♪ I wanna know ♪</i>

116
00:06:58.627 --> 00:07:02.380
{\an8}<i>♪ Have you ever seen the rain? ♪</i>

117
00:07:05.300 --> 00:07:06.676
[phone chimes]

118
00:07:10.472 --> 00:07:14.351
[Doug] <i>Griff. it's Doug. I just ran</i>
<i>into your mom at the supermarket.</i>

119
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:16.311
<i>She said you booked a big gig today.</i>

120
00:07:17.020 --> 00:07:20.065
<i>I'm proud of you. bud.
Everyone in Buffalo misses you.</i>

121
00:07:20.148 --> 00:07:22.400
<i>I love you. Come visit. man!</i>

122
00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:25.820
- [knocks]
- [gasps] Jesus. Jerry.

123
00:07:25.904 --> 00:07:29.407
Doug. what is this thing about…
there's some kind of sewer monster?

124
00:07:30.533 --> 00:07:31.618
Oh. boy.

125
00:07:33.036 --> 00:07:34.412
[sighs] Doug.

126
00:07:35.622 --> 00:07:38.249
Look. I get that this is not
what you dreamed about

127
00:07:38.333 --> 00:07:39.542
when you were a kid.

128
00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:42.253
But dreams. they go. Huh?

129
00:07:42.337 --> 00:07:44.214
Now. I'll be retiring soon.

130
00:07:44.297 --> 00:07:48.385
And. Doug. it is only a matter of time
before all this is yours.

131
00:07:48.468 --> 00:07:49.511
- [Doug] Really?
- Yeah.

132
00:07:49.594 --> 00:07:51.638
Look around. Take it all in.

133
00:07:53.056 --> 00:07:54.099
And imagine.

134
00:07:55.850 --> 00:07:59.062
If you do it right.
it's a pretty sweet setup we got here.

135
00:07:59.145 --> 00:08:02.649
This is a B. and maybe
even a B+ life we're talking about.

136
00:08:04.901 --> 00:08:05.735
Hmm.

137
00:08:05.819 --> 00:08:08.863
[wife] Are you sure you don't
wanna do anything for your birthday?

138
00:08:09.364 --> 00:08:11.700
You used to make me
celebrate your half-birthdays.

139
00:08:11.783 --> 00:08:13.243
[Doug chuckles]

140
00:08:13.326 --> 00:08:14.536
Let's go get a beer.

141
00:08:15.453 --> 00:08:16.621
Or something.

142
00:08:17.163 --> 00:08:18.039
[gasps]

143
00:08:18.123 --> 00:08:20.583
Maybe we just watch
that new mountain climbing doc.

144
00:08:20.667 --> 00:08:23.128
About the lady
that falls to her own death?

145
00:08:24.045 --> 00:08:25.046
Yeah.

146
00:08:25.547 --> 00:08:29.926
Fine. we can do the one about
the free diver in the Maldives.

147
00:08:30.010 --> 00:08:32.512
Who drowns? Jesus Christ. Doug.

148
00:08:32.595 --> 00:08:34.699
I don't know. Let's just take a gummy
and go to bed early.

149
00:08:34.723 --> 00:08:36.224
Surprise!

150
00:08:36.307 --> 00:08:38.309
- [cheering]
- [upbeat music playing]

151
00:08:38.393 --> 00:08:40.311
Oh. my God. Malie. No!

152
00:08:40.395 --> 00:08:42.856
Oh. yes. Yes. you love a good.
big birthday party.

153
00:08:42.939 --> 00:08:44.816
Dad. should've seen your face.

154
00:08:44.899 --> 00:08:46.609
- You knew about this?
- It was my idea.

155
00:08:46.693 --> 00:08:48.737
- Buddy. take my coat. please. Thank you.
- Okay.

156
00:08:48.820 --> 00:08:50.113
Hey! How are you?

157
00:08:50.196 --> 00:08:52.657
- Yeah. Happy birthday!
- Jesus. Kenny. My back! [Laughs]

158
00:08:52.741 --> 00:08:55.326
- I'm sorry.
- [gasps] No! That's not…

159
00:08:55.410 --> 00:08:57.746
The actual lotion. The actual basket.

160
00:08:57.829 --> 00:08:59.789
"It puts the lotion in the basket"?

161
00:08:59.873 --> 00:09:01.624
- eBay. buddy.
- Dude. that is sick.

162
00:09:01.708 --> 00:09:03.585
Yeah. no. that is actually sick.

163
00:09:03.668 --> 00:09:04.878
Oh!

164
00:09:04.961 --> 00:09:06.171
Happy birthday. Dougie.

165
00:09:06.254 --> 00:09:08.339
[Doug] Thanks for making the trek. Claire.

166
00:09:08.423 --> 00:09:10.884
Oh. you know I love Buffalo
this time of year.

167
00:09:10.967 --> 00:09:13.595
The slush. the hypothermia.

168
00:09:13.678 --> 00:09:14.846
What's up? No Trent?

169
00:09:14.929 --> 00:09:16.139
No Trent.

170
00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:17.348
Ever again. in fact.

171
00:09:17.849 --> 00:09:20.101
- He started banging his dental hygienist.
- Ugh.

172
00:09:20.185 --> 00:09:23.021
Anyway. tonight is all about you. baby.

173
00:09:23.104 --> 00:09:24.981
- It's about me.
- It's about you.

174
00:09:25.065 --> 00:09:26.399
[gasps]

175
00:09:26.483 --> 00:09:27.776
[laughs]

176
00:09:27.859 --> 00:09:30.528
You came! Here you are. Oh. my God.

177
00:09:30.612 --> 00:09:31.529
It's been too long. pal.

178
00:09:31.613 --> 00:09:33.948
It's so good to see you.
It has been way too long.

179
00:09:34.032 --> 00:09:35.033
Happy birthday.

180
00:09:35.116 --> 00:09:36.910
Thank you for coming out here.

181
00:09:36.993 --> 00:09:38.345
- Think I'm gonna miss this? Never.
- Oh.

182
00:09:38.369 --> 00:09:39.954
We got a lot of catching up to do.

183
00:09:40.455 --> 00:09:45.919
Many years ago. a group of young.
passionate artists had a vision.

184
00:09:46.002 --> 00:09:51.549
It was a vision that's not
particularly original or even. uh. good.

185
00:09:51.633 --> 00:09:53.551
- but it was theirs.
- [guests chuckle]

186
00:09:53.635 --> 00:09:56.805
And so they made that vision a reality.

187
00:09:57.430 --> 00:09:59.599
And. without further ado.

188
00:09:59.682 --> 00:10:04.729
I present to you
a completely unrestored print

189
00:10:04.813 --> 00:10:09.984
of 13-year-old Doug McCallister's
masterpiece. <i>The Quatch</i>.

190
00:10:10.068 --> 00:10:11.236
- [gasping]
- What?

191
00:10:11.319 --> 00:10:12.960
I thought we lost all the copies of that!

192
00:10:12.987 --> 00:10:13.988
- No way.
- Nope.

193
00:10:14.072 --> 00:10:16.866
I found it in my mom's garage.
It was stuck in the player.

194
00:10:16.950 --> 00:10:19.285
Are we sure this is okay
for the kids to watch?

195
00:10:19.369 --> 00:10:20.245
Who gives a shit?

196
00:10:20.328 --> 00:10:22.288
Mrs. Brown had us bleep all the swears

197
00:10:22.372 --> 00:10:23.766
so we could show it
at the school assembly.

198
00:10:23.790 --> 00:10:25.059
Yeah. which didn't make much sense

199
00:10:25.083 --> 00:10:27.627
because we were very clear
about it being R-rated.

200
00:10:27.710 --> 00:10:30.213
- Happy birthday. pal.
- [laughs] This isn't happening.

201
00:10:30.296 --> 00:10:32.215
[Griff] Oh. it's happening. Here we go.

202
00:10:32.298 --> 00:10:33.758
[laughs]

203
00:10:33.842 --> 00:10:34.926
- God.
- Here. sit.

204
00:10:35.009 --> 00:10:37.178
I'm gonna kill you. [Gasps]

205
00:10:37.262 --> 00:10:38.930
[guests laugh]

206
00:10:40.098 --> 00:10:41.474
I haven't changed a bit.

207
00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:42.934
[all laughing]

208
00:10:43.017 --> 00:10:45.270
<i>- Holy mother♪♪♪♪♪♪!</i>
- Oh!

209
00:10:45.353 --> 00:10:47.856
- [young Griff] <i>Look at the grass!</i>
- [Doug] Hot on the trail!

210
00:10:47.939 --> 00:10:50.316
- Look out for the quatch.
- [guest] Here we go.

211
00:10:50.400 --> 00:10:54.279
<i>Before you ♪♪♪♪♪♪♪ strike me. I need to
♪♪♪♪♪♪♪ ask you one ♪♪♪♪♪♪♪ thing.</i>

212
00:10:54.362 --> 00:10:55.613
<i>You got some ♪♪♪♪♪♪♪ bite left?</i>

213
00:10:55.697 --> 00:10:56.823
<i>Or you all ♪♪♪♪♪♪♪ bark?</i>

214
00:10:56.906 --> 00:10:57.740
[Doug] Boom!

215
00:10:57.824 --> 00:10:59.951
Damn. we'd been watching
a lot of Scorsese.

216
00:11:00.577 --> 00:11:03.037
We didn't quite have
the ear for it. did we?

217
00:11:03.121 --> 00:11:05.373
<i>- I need to tell you something.
- What is it?</i>

218
00:11:05.874 --> 00:11:08.585
[young Claire] <i>That I love you.</i>
<i>I've always loved you.</i>

219
00:11:08.668 --> 00:11:10.336
<i>And I always ♪♪♪♪♪♪♪ will.</i>

220
00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:11.897
[young Griff] <i>I ♪♪♪♪♪♪♪ love you too.</i>

221
00:11:11.921 --> 00:11:13.840
<i>Now. kiss me. woman.</i>

222
00:11:13.923 --> 00:11:15.300
[guests chuckle]

223
00:11:15.383 --> 00:11:18.011
So much charisma. Already. you had it.

224
00:11:18.094 --> 00:11:20.597
I still can't believe I let Doug talk me
into doing that.

225
00:11:20.680 --> 00:11:22.521
What are you talking about?
That was your idea.

226
00:11:23.933 --> 00:11:25.977
- [guests chuckling]
- [Doug] Yeah!

227
00:11:26.603 --> 00:11:28.730
<i>- It's coming for us.</i>
- [young Claire] <i>We're trapped.</i>

228
00:11:28.813 --> 00:11:30.499
[young Kenny]
<i>What the hell are we gonna do?</i>

229
00:11:30.523 --> 00:11:31.608
[laughter continues]

230
00:11:31.691 --> 00:11:32.984
- [Claire] No!
- [Doug] Yes.

231
00:11:33.067 --> 00:11:35.528
<i>Oh. my God. We're all gonna die!</i>

232
00:11:35.612 --> 00:11:39.365
[dramatic music playing on TV]

233
00:11:39.449 --> 00:11:40.992
This is where it gets real.

234
00:11:41.492 --> 00:11:43.745
<i>Not on my watch. mister.</i>

235
00:11:45.496 --> 00:11:47.206
- Boom!
- Yeah!

236
00:11:47.290 --> 00:11:49.083
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

237
00:11:49.167 --> 00:11:50.543
[guest] Amazing!

238
00:11:51.794 --> 00:11:53.171
[guest] So good!

239
00:11:54.714 --> 00:11:56.633
Whoo!

240
00:11:58.509 --> 00:12:01.429
That's probably the best birthday gift
I've ever received.

241
00:12:01.512 --> 00:12:03.873
- I didn't even know it existed.
- Well. I'm giving it to you.

242
00:12:03.932 --> 00:12:05.934
Plus the TV 'cause you can't get it out.

243
00:12:06.935 --> 00:12:08.144
- Yay!
- [Kenny] Yes!

244
00:12:10.772 --> 00:12:11.772
[Claire exclaims]

245
00:12:11.814 --> 00:12:14.943
- It was right after. you know…
- Right after senior year of college.

246
00:12:15.026 --> 00:12:18.529
Yes. that's when <i>Anaconda</i> came out.
Remember? We saw it like 30 times.

247
00:12:18.613 --> 00:12:20.490
Put it right there alongside the classics.

248
00:12:20.573 --> 00:12:22.450
Totally. How about that cast? Come on.

249
00:12:22.533 --> 00:12:26.037
- J.Lo. Ice Cube. Owen Wilson. Stoltz.
- Oh. for sure.

250
00:12:26.120 --> 00:12:27.330
I mean. it's a murderers' row.

251
00:12:27.413 --> 00:12:32.168
Plus. that snake was like a metaphor
for our lives at that moment.

252
00:12:34.212 --> 00:12:36.547
Like. how life is coming at you. you know.

253
00:12:36.631 --> 00:12:39.509
hunting you and forcing you. like.

254
00:12:39.592 --> 00:12:40.760
off your

255
00:12:41.636 --> 00:12:43.846
like your parents'
health insurance and stuff.

256
00:12:43.930 --> 00:12:45.306
[gulps]

257
00:12:46.933 --> 00:12:48.702
- [Kenny] I don't know…
- [Doug] No. that's true.

258
00:12:48.726 --> 00:12:50.120
- Yeah. that's…
- [Doug] Oh. it was like that.

259
00:12:50.144 --> 00:12:51.580
- [Claire] That's right. Kenny.
- Whatever.

260
00:12:51.604 --> 00:12:55.483
How about that accent by Jon Voight?
How about that? That was a choice.

261
00:12:55.566 --> 00:12:58.528
"They wrap around you
until you get the privilege

262
00:12:58.611 --> 00:13:00.613
- of hearing your bones break…
- "Bones break

263
00:13:00.697 --> 00:13:06.536
"before the power of embrace
causes your veins to explode."

264
00:13:07.203 --> 00:13:08.204
Sorry.

265
00:13:10.832 --> 00:13:12.166
I have the rights to <i>Anaconda.</i>

266
00:13:14.752 --> 00:13:15.752
What?

267
00:13:16.212 --> 00:13:17.880
I have the rights to <i>Anaconda.</i>

268
00:13:19.382 --> 00:13:25.471
Yeah. Apparently. the movie was based
on a novel by some dead Japanese guy.

269
00:13:25.555 --> 00:13:28.558
And my agent introduced me to his widow.

270
00:13:29.392 --> 00:13:33.229
Unbelievably. she… she was such a fan
of the four episodes

271
00:13:33.312 --> 00:13:34.522
that I did on <i>S.W.A.T…</i>

272
00:13:34.605 --> 00:13:36.649
- Who isn't?
- …that she gave me the rights.

273
00:13:36.733 --> 00:13:39.360
Oh. dude.
So. what are you gonna do with them?

274
00:13:39.861 --> 00:13:41.237
Uh. well. not me.

275
00:13:42.864 --> 00:13:43.864
Us.

276
00:13:45.158 --> 00:13:48.119
We're gonna reboot the thing. Indie-style.

277
00:13:48.202 --> 00:13:52.540
Three weeks. run-and-gun in the Amazon.
Skeletal crew.

278
00:13:52.623 --> 00:13:55.877
Claire. you and I can star.
Kenny. you shoot it. Doug. you direct.

279
00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:58.337
Huh? Come on. What do you say?

280
00:13:58.421 --> 00:14:00.590
I mean. it's a wonderful idea
in theory. but…

281
00:14:00.673 --> 00:14:04.093
I'm in! I can get time off from work.

282
00:14:04.177 --> 00:14:05.803
Yes. you can. Kenny. Sweet!

283
00:14:05.887 --> 00:14:09.474
Kenny. what are you talking about?
You're in? He's not… No. He's not in.

284
00:14:09.557 --> 00:14:13.186
He says one thing and you're in already.
You're going to the Amazon.

285
00:14:13.269 --> 00:14:15.521
- [Doug] He's not in.
- What do you say. Claire?

286
00:14:15.605 --> 00:14:17.148
- I… I just…
- Come on.

287
00:14:17.231 --> 00:14:19.025
I don't know
if I'm in the right headspace…

288
00:14:19.108 --> 00:14:20.502
- Of course you are.
- …with the divorce.

289
00:14:20.526 --> 00:14:21.962
Of course you're not
in the right headspace.

290
00:14:21.986 --> 00:14:24.238
That's the best headspace.
Are you kidding me?

291
00:14:24.322 --> 00:14:27.575
Come on. it's like <i>Eat Pray Love</i>
and… shit.

292
00:14:27.658 --> 00:14:28.659
Come on.

293
00:14:29.660 --> 00:14:31.412
You know what? I'm in.

294
00:14:31.496 --> 00:14:32.955
- What? Really?
- Yes

295
00:14:33.039 --> 00:14:33.915
- Sweet.
- [Claire] Yeah.

296
00:14:33.998 --> 00:14:36.334
I mean. my life is totally shit anyway so…

297
00:14:36.417 --> 00:14:38.294
- God. I'm so happy to hear that.
- Hmm.

298
00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:40.880
I mean. not that your life is shit.
but that you're in.

299
00:14:41.381 --> 00:14:43.007
Besides. as soon as Doug says yes.

300
00:14:43.091 --> 00:14:45.027
we'll probably need you
to finance this whole thing.

301
00:14:45.051 --> 00:14:46.677
- [Claire] What?
- [mouthing] Thank you.

302
00:14:46.761 --> 00:14:47.761
Doug?

303
00:14:51.849 --> 00:14:53.935
[Doug] Griff. I'm sorry.

304
00:14:54.519 --> 00:14:58.272
I got responsibilities.
I got Malie. Charlie. my job.

305
00:14:58.356 --> 00:15:00.775
I know. Making. uh. wedding videos.

306
00:15:00.858 --> 00:15:02.276
Films. Right.

307
00:15:03.069 --> 00:15:04.404
It's a good life. you know?

308
00:15:05.113 --> 00:15:06.656
It's a B. B+ life.

309
00:15:08.241 --> 00:15:09.700
B. B+ life?

310
00:15:11.285 --> 00:15:12.495
It's a good life.

311
00:15:14.122 --> 00:15:15.498
Do you remember when we were kids

312
00:15:15.581 --> 00:15:17.226
and we would stay up
till 4:00 in the morning.

313
00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:19.530
hanging out in your mom's basement
watching horror movies?

314
00:15:20.378 --> 00:15:22.130
Scaring the shit out of ourselves.

315
00:15:22.213 --> 00:15:24.465
<i>Texas Chainsaw</i> on. like. repeat.

316
00:15:24.549 --> 00:15:26.884
Now we have the chance
to make one ourselves.

317
00:15:27.885 --> 00:15:30.763
Dude. it's what we dreamed about
ever since we were little kids.

318
00:15:32.515 --> 00:15:33.683
I hear ya.

319
00:15:34.684 --> 00:15:36.936
But we're not kids anymore. Griff.

320
00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:38.855
I'm sorry.

321
00:15:41.149 --> 00:15:42.859
Yeah. I know. All right.

322
00:15:43.860 --> 00:15:44.902
I just…

323
00:15:45.820 --> 00:15:46.988
I get it. I do.

324
00:15:47.905 --> 00:15:49.073
I get it.

325
00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:56.914
Still watching <i>The Quatch</i>.

326
00:15:59.917 --> 00:16:01.252
[chuckling]

327
00:16:02.253 --> 00:16:04.755
Charlie. why don't you go
check on those cookies?

328
00:16:04.839 --> 00:16:07.300
[sighs] Okay. but I'm pausing it. so…

329
00:16:08.342 --> 00:16:09.343
Don't touch it.

330
00:16:10.428 --> 00:16:12.513
Gonna need some ice-cold milch with that.

331
00:16:12.597 --> 00:16:13.848
[Charlie] You got it.

332
00:16:15.057 --> 00:16:16.559
- What are you doing?
- [Doug] What?

333
00:16:16.642 --> 00:16:17.977
Just go make the movie.

334
00:16:18.060 --> 00:16:19.353
Malie.

335
00:16:19.437 --> 00:16:21.981
Come on. Every time you watch this thing.
you light up.

336
00:16:22.064 --> 00:16:24.775
Like I haven't seen you light up
in a long time.

337
00:16:24.859 --> 00:16:28.654
So what? I'm supposed to chase
some Hollywood fantasy I had as a kid?

338
00:16:28.738 --> 00:16:30.948
Waste a bunch of money and time.
and for what?

339
00:16:31.032 --> 00:16:33.242
In the end. what's it gonna change?

340
00:16:35.828 --> 00:16:36.829
Okay.

341
00:16:38.206 --> 00:16:39.207
Okay.

342
00:16:39.749 --> 00:16:40.750
Okay.

343
00:16:43.127 --> 00:16:46.756
- [mouse clicks]
- [upbeat music playing on video]

344
00:16:46.839 --> 00:16:48.299
[bride and groom chuckling]

345
00:16:48.382 --> 00:16:50.510
[bride] <i>We hope you come to celebrate…</i>

346
00:16:50.593 --> 00:16:51.593
[groom] <i>As we become…</i>

347
00:16:51.636 --> 00:16:53.012
[both] <i>The Hansons.</i>

348
00:16:54.597 --> 00:16:56.307
Holy shit.

349
00:16:59.435 --> 00:17:00.520
[sighs]

350
00:17:00.603 --> 00:17:02.897
["I Don't Want To Wait"
by Paula Cole playing]

351
00:17:08.361 --> 00:17:10.530
[sings] <i>♪…what will it be? ♪</i>

352
00:17:11.781 --> 00:17:16.869
♪ <i>I don't want to wait</i>
<i>For our lives to be over </i> ♪

353
00:17:16.953 --> 00:17:19.455
- What am I singing?
- [knocking on door]

354
00:17:20.957 --> 00:17:21.958
[Griff] Hey. dude.

355
00:17:24.126 --> 00:17:26.337
I don't want to wait. man. [Panting]

356
00:17:27.421 --> 00:17:30.675
Our lives could be. like… over.

357
00:17:31.300 --> 00:17:32.593
What are you talking about?

358
00:17:32.677 --> 00:17:36.180
The <i>Anaconda </i>thing.
You were serious. right?

359
00:17:37.181 --> 00:17:38.224
Yes. very.

360
00:17:38.307 --> 00:17:39.517
Then let's do it.

361
00:17:40.726 --> 00:17:42.520
Let's reboot <i>Anaconda.</i>

362
00:17:43.437 --> 00:17:45.481
Yes! Yes.

363
00:17:49.860 --> 00:17:52.863
[lively music playing]

364
00:17:56.409 --> 00:18:01.747
["Baby Got Back" by Sir Mix-a-Lot playing]

365
00:18:03.916 --> 00:18:05.876
{\an8}<i>♪ My anaconda don't ♪</i>

366
00:18:06.669 --> 00:18:09.839
All right. budget-wise. soup to nuts.
what does it cost to get this thing made?

367
00:18:09.922 --> 00:18:13.843
I figure we need three weeks of shooting.
Some VFX. some SFX.

368
00:18:13.926 --> 00:18:17.138
a riverboat. a riverboat captain.
travel to and from a jungle.

369
00:18:17.221 --> 00:18:20.891
and a gigantic real snake.
preferably a rental.

370
00:18:20.975 --> 00:18:22.476
- Rental. copy.
- All in.

371
00:18:22.560 --> 00:18:24.520
two. two-and-a-half million dollars.

372
00:18:24.604 --> 00:18:26.188
[whistles] That sounds right.

373
00:18:26.272 --> 00:18:30.568
- We've approved a loan for you for up to…
- [keyboard clicking]

374
00:18:30.651 --> 00:18:32.320
$9.400.

375
00:18:32.903 --> 00:18:33.779
Yes!

376
00:18:33.863 --> 00:18:36.574
I've revised the budget down to

377
00:18:36.657 --> 00:18:37.992
$43.000 all in.

378
00:18:38.075 --> 00:18:39.243
That sounds more right.

379
00:18:39.327 --> 00:18:41.221
[Doug] <i>Now. the film does have</i>
<i>to be scary. right?</i>

380
00:18:41.245 --> 00:18:45.249
Terrifying. But it can't just be about
a giant snake killing people.

381
00:18:45.333 --> 00:18:46.584
- Exactly.
- You know?

382
00:18:46.667 --> 00:18:48.711
It has to be about something. right?

383
00:18:48.794 --> 00:18:49.795
Right.

384
00:18:50.671 --> 00:18:52.089
I mean…

385
00:18:52.173 --> 00:18:53.215
- Themes.
- Themes.

386
00:18:54.634 --> 00:18:55.968
- Come on.
- Like grief.

387
00:18:56.052 --> 00:18:56.927
What about revenge?

388
00:18:57.011 --> 00:18:59.680
In terms of themes.
that's like one of the top ones.

389
00:18:59.764 --> 00:19:01.599
- Oh. my God. I got a good one.
- Hit me.

390
00:19:01.682 --> 00:19:03.601
Intergenerational trauma.

391
00:19:03.684 --> 00:19:05.728
[scoffs] I love intergenerational trauma.

392
00:19:05.811 --> 00:19:07.492
Who doesn't love intergenerational trauma?

393
00:19:07.521 --> 00:19:09.732
- It's the best.
- We're onto something here.

394
00:19:10.816 --> 00:19:12.026
[music stops]

395
00:19:14.028 --> 00:19:16.155
[breathes deeply]

396
00:19:17.865 --> 00:19:19.617
This is a masterpiece.

397
00:19:19.700 --> 00:19:21.535
You're a goddamn genius. I love it.

398
00:19:21.619 --> 00:19:23.037
- Don't change a word.
- Not a word.

399
00:19:23.120 --> 00:19:25.474
Dude. you killed it. It's scary.
emotional. it's funny when it needs to be.

400
00:19:25.498 --> 00:19:27.541
- Romantic.
- Dude. thank you.

401
00:19:27.625 --> 00:19:28.751
Hey. Doug…

402
00:19:29.710 --> 00:19:34.215
[exhales]
I know that we had our little dust up. but…

403
00:19:35.424 --> 00:19:37.635
[sighs] I need to shoot this film. man.

404
00:19:37.718 --> 00:19:38.719
[Griff] Dustup?

405
00:19:39.470 --> 00:19:42.890
Yeah. He fired me
from the wedding video stuff

406
00:19:42.973 --> 00:19:45.309
'cause I got a little wasted.

407
00:19:45.393 --> 00:19:47.103
He knocked over the wedding cake.

408
00:19:48.104 --> 00:19:50.940
- But I'm dealing with it.
- Like. getting sober?

409
00:19:51.023 --> 00:19:52.024
Yes.

410
00:19:52.108 --> 00:19:54.193
Well. I mean. Buffalo sober.

411
00:19:54.276 --> 00:19:56.570
- Buffalo sober?
- Mm-hmm. Just beer and wine.

412
00:19:58.155 --> 00:20:01.826
And then some of the lighter liquors.
But definitely not all of 'em.

413
00:20:03.244 --> 00:20:04.244
I'm proud of you.

414
00:20:05.705 --> 00:20:06.705
Doug?

415
00:20:07.373 --> 00:20:08.791
[inhales deeply]

416
00:20:08.874 --> 00:20:11.627
If I'm being honest.
I enabled you a little bit.

417
00:20:11.711 --> 00:20:14.171
Of course you get a second chance.
Let's do this.

418
00:20:15.089 --> 00:20:16.132
- Nice!
- Thank you. man.

419
00:20:16.215 --> 00:20:18.759
- [horn honking]
- [Malie] Car's here.

420
00:20:18.843 --> 00:20:22.555
And you have the Mefloquine. right?
You only take that once a week.

421
00:20:22.638 --> 00:20:25.015
- Hey. Dad. I almost forgot.
- Hmm?

422
00:20:25.099 --> 00:20:29.270
- [Doug] Talk to me.
- But I got you… this.

423
00:20:29.353 --> 00:20:30.771
What?

424
00:20:30.855 --> 00:20:32.064
[Charlie] I know. Pretty sick.

425
00:20:32.732 --> 00:20:35.401
"World's greatest Doug."

426
00:20:35.484 --> 00:20:38.237
- I thought it should say. "Dad."
- Whatever. man. it's funny.

427
00:20:38.320 --> 00:20:40.531
- I love it. It's much better.
- [Charlie chuckles]

428
00:20:41.198 --> 00:20:45.661
["Welcome To Brazil" playing]

429
00:20:58.048 --> 00:20:59.842
[monkey chattering]

430
00:21:02.720 --> 00:21:05.014
[music fades]

431
00:21:05.097 --> 00:21:08.267
[people chattering indistinctly
in Portuguese]

432
00:21:11.937 --> 00:21:13.147
[sighs]

433
00:21:16.358 --> 00:21:17.860
[intriguing music playing]

434
00:21:17.943 --> 00:21:19.612
- [Doug] So it begins.
- Yeah!

435
00:21:20.279 --> 00:21:21.197
- [Doug] Oh. yeah.
- All right

436
00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:22.281
- [Claire] Whoo!
- Made it.

437
00:21:23.449 --> 00:21:26.009
- [Griff] Whoa. We're here.
- [Doug] That's what I'm talkin' about!

438
00:21:26.035 --> 00:21:28.162
- Brasília!
- [Kenny] Oh.

439
00:21:28.245 --> 00:21:30.831
So. hey. I was reading about anacondas
on the plane.

440
00:21:30.915 --> 00:21:33.793
Basically.
they wait in the water for days.

441
00:21:33.876 --> 00:21:36.879
stalking their prey.
never moving. just waiting.

442
00:21:36.962 --> 00:21:38.047
and then when a prey comes…

443
00:21:38.130 --> 00:21:39.006
[imitates snake constricting]

444
00:21:39.089 --> 00:21:40.007
…snatch and grab.

445
00:21:40.090 --> 00:21:42.811
Thousand pounds of pressure.
Think you're gonna get away? You're not.

446
00:21:42.885 --> 00:21:45.721
Crushing you. Oxygen leaving your lungs.

447
00:21:45.805 --> 00:21:47.306
[imitates suffocating]

448
00:21:47.389 --> 00:21:48.933
Oh. God. it's terrible.

449
00:21:49.016 --> 00:21:51.393
- So. like in the movie <i>Anaconda</i>.
- Yeah. exactly.

450
00:21:51.477 --> 00:21:52.561
So it's real?

451
00:21:52.645 --> 00:21:53.938
[passerby] Yeah. it's all real.

452
00:21:55.856 --> 00:21:59.026
- Very real.
- [tense music playing]

453
00:21:59.109 --> 00:22:01.779
There's this story about this woman…

454
00:22:02.321 --> 00:22:03.405
God bless her.

455
00:22:04.073 --> 00:22:06.951
The snake wraps around her so tight…

456
00:22:08.619 --> 00:22:10.079
The eyeballs just…

457
00:22:10.621 --> 00:22:11.747
[imitates explosion]

458
00:22:11.831 --> 00:22:13.749
- No.
- No way.

459
00:22:13.833 --> 00:22:16.877
- Yeah. it was my grandmother. Sylvana.
- Shit.

460
00:22:17.419 --> 00:22:20.089
Horrible grandmother. But still sad.

461
00:22:20.589 --> 00:22:21.589
[Kenny] Huh.

462
00:22:21.632 --> 00:22:22.800
I'm sorry. who are you?

463
00:22:23.467 --> 00:22:26.220
Oh. I'm sorry. Carlos Santiago.
Yeah. you can call me Santiago.

464
00:22:26.303 --> 00:22:28.556
- Hey! It's Kenny.
- [Santiago] Yeah. hey.

465
00:22:28.639 --> 00:22:31.183
- Kenny from the phone. Hey.
- Kenny. Kenny. hey.

466
00:22:31.267 --> 00:22:33.394
- Hi.
- Yeah. this is our snake handler.

467
00:22:33.477 --> 00:22:34.353
[Claire. Doug] Oh!

468
00:22:34.436 --> 00:22:36.248
- [Claire] Thank God.
- He's supposed to be the best.

469
00:22:36.272 --> 00:22:38.357
No. "Supposed to be"?
We have a joker here.

470
00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:40.859
No. I am the best. Yes.

471
00:22:40.943 --> 00:22:42.170
- Oh. That's good.
- [Kenny] Yeah.

472
00:22:42.194 --> 00:22:44.280
So. welcome to Brazil.

473
00:22:45.406 --> 00:22:46.782
Let's meet the snake.

474
00:22:46.865 --> 00:22:50.119
[people chattering indistinctly]

475
00:22:51.579 --> 00:22:55.708
[tense music playing]

476
00:22:59.211 --> 00:23:01.672
[in Portuguese] Go around. we'll find her.

477
00:23:08.304 --> 00:23:11.515
[patrons speaking Portuguese]

478
00:23:19.148 --> 00:23:20.232
[music stops]

479
00:23:20.316 --> 00:23:23.193
[in English] When I found him.
he was dying of starvation.

480
00:23:23.986 --> 00:23:28.282
His food supply destroyed by gold miners
who put mercury in the river.

481
00:23:28.365 --> 00:23:31.201
- [Griff] Gold miners?
- Gold mining poisons our land.

482
00:23:31.994 --> 00:23:34.330
[Santiago]
Their greed almost killed my snake.

483
00:23:34.872 --> 00:23:39.168
- Oh.
- But I fed him. I nursed him back to life.

484
00:23:39.251 --> 00:23:42.796
and in many ways. he did the same for me.

485
00:23:42.880 --> 00:23:45.507
Ah. yes. A tale as old as time.

486
00:23:45.591 --> 00:23:46.842
Saved by a snake. [Chuckles]

487
00:23:49.762 --> 00:23:51.180
What's your name?

488
00:23:51.263 --> 00:23:52.264
What's… Uh. Griff.

489
00:23:52.348 --> 00:23:54.516
Okay. Griff. He's not only a snake.

490
00:23:55.225 --> 00:23:57.394
He's my tiny giant. my friend.

491
00:23:58.312 --> 00:24:02.107
One of the most important creatures
of the herpetological world.

492
00:24:02.691 --> 00:24:04.276
No. of course… I… Sure.

493
00:24:04.360 --> 00:24:07.112
I didn't… I wasn't trying to… I… Yes.

494
00:24:07.196 --> 00:24:10.282
Okay. Let me introduce you.

495
00:24:12.117 --> 00:24:13.661
[trunk opens]

496
00:24:13.744 --> 00:24:15.037
Heitor.

497
00:24:15.120 --> 00:24:17.915
- [Claire] Heitor?
- Oh. my goodness.

498
00:24:17.998 --> 00:24:19.583
Hey. cutie.

499
00:24:19.667 --> 00:24:21.669
- Oh. no. Not cutie.
- Oh. my…

500
00:24:21.752 --> 00:24:23.587
- [Doug] Oh…
- [all exclaim]

501
00:24:23.671 --> 00:24:26.382
Oh. hell. yes! This thing is nuts!

502
00:24:26.465 --> 00:24:29.802
There are rumors of 'condas even bigger.

503
00:24:29.885 --> 00:24:32.554
Maybe four or five times this size.

504
00:24:33.972 --> 00:24:35.158
Go ahead. Kenny from the phone.

505
00:24:35.182 --> 00:24:38.435
Um. is it true that they
regurgitate their prey?

506
00:24:38.519 --> 00:24:40.396
Um. sometimes.

507
00:24:40.479 --> 00:24:42.356
I mean. if you're lucky.

508
00:24:42.439 --> 00:24:44.066
you die right away because of

509
00:24:44.149 --> 00:24:45.442
[groans] suffocation.

510
00:24:46.068 --> 00:24:50.072
But only the unlucky ones survive.

511
00:24:50.155 --> 00:24:51.365
Unlucky?

512
00:24:53.033 --> 00:24:57.413
Yeah. because then
you might actually be conscious

513
00:24:57.496 --> 00:25:01.291
when the snake comes back
to finish you off.

514
00:25:01.917 --> 00:25:03.669
- [Doug] Gotcha.
- [Claire] Ooh.

515
00:25:03.752 --> 00:25:04.795
Better to die.

516
00:25:05.587 --> 00:25:08.090
[tense music playing]

517
00:25:14.054 --> 00:25:16.765
- [Kenny] Look at that boat!
- [Doug] This is money in the bank. baby.

518
00:25:23.522 --> 00:25:24.857
[keys jingle]

519
00:25:31.280 --> 00:25:33.073
- [music stops]
- [patrons chattering]

520
00:25:34.408 --> 00:25:36.910
[tense music playing]

521
00:25:36.994 --> 00:25:38.829
[thuds]

522
00:25:42.499 --> 00:25:44.334
Hey. Let me ask you a question.

523
00:25:44.418 --> 00:25:46.670
- Um. our snake guy…
- Mmm?

524
00:25:47.296 --> 00:25:50.132
…does he seem kind of bat shit crazy?

525
00:25:50.215 --> 00:25:52.509
I mean. he's best friends with a snake.

526
00:25:52.593 --> 00:25:54.028
- Of course he's a little quirky.
- Yeah.

527
00:25:54.052 --> 00:25:55.053
But I like him.

528
00:25:55.137 --> 00:25:55.971
- Really?
- Yeah.

529
00:25:56.054 --> 00:25:57.055
But then again.

530
00:25:57.139 --> 00:25:59.183
I used up all my vacation days

531
00:25:59.266 --> 00:26:02.478
to come make a self-financed snake movie
with you three. so…

532
00:26:02.561 --> 00:26:04.748
- Yeah. your judgment is really off.
- My judgment is off.

533
00:26:04.772 --> 00:26:05.874
- It always has been.
- Exactly.

534
00:26:05.898 --> 00:26:07.917
[Doug] Anybody talk to the captain?
It's time to shoot.

535
00:26:07.941 --> 00:26:09.693
I'll reach out again. boss.

536
00:26:09.777 --> 00:26:10.903
- [Doug exclaims]
- [chuckles]

537
00:26:11.445 --> 00:26:13.113
Hi. guys. My name is Ana.

538
00:26:13.197 --> 00:26:15.032
I believe you spoke
to my father on the phone?

539
00:26:15.616 --> 00:26:17.201
Bruno? That's your dad?

540
00:26:17.910 --> 00:26:19.012
Yeah. he sends his apologies.

541
00:26:19.036 --> 00:26:20.954
- but he's at the hospital.
- Oh.

542
00:26:21.038 --> 00:26:22.956
- Oh. I'm sorry.
- Unfortunately.

543
00:26:23.040 --> 00:26:24.680
you'll have to make other accommodations.

544
00:26:24.750 --> 00:26:27.878
'cause I need to take this boat upriver
for a routine service.

545
00:26:27.961 --> 00:26:29.421
But I can assure you a full refund.

546
00:26:29.505 --> 00:26:30.339
No. wait. Wait.

547
00:26:30.422 --> 00:26:32.466
- Everything else is booked.
- [Griff] Yeah.

548
00:26:32.549 --> 00:26:34.343
And… and we're gonna shoot a movie.

549
00:26:34.426 --> 00:26:36.303
It's a… it's a reboot of <i>Anaconda</i>.

550
00:26:36.386 --> 00:26:38.114
Technically.
it's more of a reimagining. but...

551
00:26:38.138 --> 00:26:40.015
It's actually more of a spiritual sequel.

552
00:26:40.098 --> 00:26:41.183
Good for you.

553
00:26:41.266 --> 00:26:43.119
- There's gotta be a way. right?
- We can crew the boat.

554
00:26:43.143 --> 00:26:44.019
There's nothing I can do…

555
00:26:44.102 --> 00:26:47.773
We have dreamed of making
this film together our entire lives.

556
00:26:47.856 --> 00:26:50.234
Please. I am begging you.

557
00:26:50.317 --> 00:26:52.277
- Please.
- Help us find another way.

558
00:26:52.361 --> 00:26:54.071
- Let's do this. but fast.
- [Doug] Okay.

559
00:26:54.154 --> 00:26:55.572
- [Claire] Yes! Let's go!
- Thank you!

560
00:26:57.282 --> 00:27:00.786
[tense music playing]

561
00:27:03.664 --> 00:27:06.333
[clanking. whirring]

562
00:27:16.301 --> 00:27:17.719
[Griff] Whoo!

563
00:27:17.803 --> 00:27:19.721
- Oh!
- [Griff] Wow!

564
00:27:19.805 --> 00:27:20.806
Yes!

565
00:27:20.889 --> 00:27:22.808
This is so beautiful.

566
00:27:22.891 --> 00:27:24.810
This is amazing. It's amazing.

567
00:27:26.353 --> 00:27:27.896
- Looks exactly…
- [Doug laughs]

568
00:27:27.980 --> 00:27:28.981
Ooh. look!

569
00:27:30.691 --> 00:27:31.984
- Kenny?
- [Kenny] Yeah. bud?

570
00:27:32.067 --> 00:27:34.069
- How did you find this boat?
- Cocktail. anyone?

571
00:27:34.152 --> 00:27:36.029
- [Griff] Nice!
- [Doug] Ah!

572
00:27:36.113 --> 00:27:37.114
[Kenny] It's a computer.

573
00:27:39.449 --> 00:27:40.617
Yes!

574
00:27:43.787 --> 00:27:45.557
[in Portuguese]
I want a list of all the boats

575
00:27:45.581 --> 00:27:48.041
that left the marina in the last 3 hours.

576
00:27:48.750 --> 00:27:49.960
Now!

577
00:27:50.669 --> 00:27:52.129
[drawer opens]

578
00:27:55.716 --> 00:27:57.509
[pensive music playing]

579
00:27:57.593 --> 00:27:59.094
- [all laughing]
- [glass clinking]

580
00:27:59.177 --> 00:28:00.298
- [Griff] Uh-oh.
- [Claire] Oh.

581
00:28:00.345 --> 00:28:02.431
[Doug] One more thing. you guys.
before we go to bed.

582
00:28:02.514 --> 00:28:04.391
We got a big day tomorrow.

583
00:28:04.474 --> 00:28:08.353
If you remember.
we had a tradition on all our films.

584
00:28:08.437 --> 00:28:10.230
The night before we started shooting.

585
00:28:10.314 --> 00:28:12.983
we would say a prayer to the movie gods.

586
00:28:13.066 --> 00:28:16.069
asking them to basically
not screw us over.

587
00:28:16.153 --> 00:28:19.364
and for the first time ever.
may they listen.

588
00:28:19.448 --> 00:28:21.033
- Come on. to the movie gods.
- Yes.

589
00:28:21.116 --> 00:28:22.409
[glasses clinking]

590
00:28:22.492 --> 00:28:24.137
- [Doug chuckles]
- [all chattering indistinctly]

591
00:28:24.161 --> 00:28:27.789
[epic music playing]

592
00:28:37.215 --> 00:28:38.484
[Kenny] All right. We're rolling.

593
00:28:38.508 --> 00:28:41.303
<i>Anaconda.</i> scene 15. take one. Slap it.

594
00:28:41.386 --> 00:28:42.888
Bella!

595
00:28:44.056 --> 00:28:47.142
- What the hell are you still doing here?
- I've come to take you home.

596
00:28:47.226 --> 00:28:50.187
It's time you stopped chasing
this mythical snake.

597
00:28:50.938 --> 00:28:53.065
And what if I'm not prone to giving up?

598
00:28:53.607 --> 00:28:54.983
I didn't see you filming there.

599
00:28:55.525 --> 00:28:56.860
What are we doing? EPK?

600
00:28:56.944 --> 00:28:58.946
Background. DVD. bonus stuff.

601
00:28:59.029 --> 00:29:03.116
<i>The Anaconda </i>is a story
of an intrepid biologist played by Claire.

602
00:29:03.200 --> 00:29:08.413
who hires an unhinged snake tracker
played by Griff.

603
00:29:08.497 --> 00:29:11.208
to hunt down and kill
a giant. mythical 'conda

604
00:29:11.291 --> 00:29:12.542
that ate her entire family.

605
00:29:12.626 --> 00:29:15.504
Come and get me. you goddamn snake!

606
00:29:15.587 --> 00:29:17.756
And on a deeper level.
it's about chasing your dreams.

607
00:29:17.839 --> 00:29:23.220
And camera set. push-ups good. and action!

608
00:29:23.303 --> 00:29:24.697
What's it like shooting with Doug again?

609
00:29:24.721 --> 00:29:26.223
He and I are best friends.

610
00:29:26.306 --> 00:29:27.700
[Griff]
<i>We've worked together our whole lives.</i>

611
00:29:27.724 --> 00:29:29.619
<i>And I went out to L.A..
and he was gonna come out.</i>

612
00:29:29.643 --> 00:29:32.312
We were gonna be a partnership.
and he… he didn't do it.

613
00:29:32.396 --> 00:29:34.356
Griff and I planned
to work together in L.A..

614
00:29:34.439 --> 00:29:36.650
but. uh. you know. life intervened.

615
00:29:36.733 --> 00:29:38.378
But it doesn't matter.
'cause now we're together

616
00:29:38.402 --> 00:29:41.613
and now we're back. we're making this.
and it's as it should be.

617
00:29:41.697 --> 00:29:44.157
- I am the insects.
- [Claire shrieks]

618
00:29:44.241 --> 00:29:46.952
The anaconda moves slow and steady.

619
00:29:47.035 --> 00:29:48.120
Sometimes it goes fast.

620
00:29:48.203 --> 00:29:50.747
Snake POV. RD. Take 1.

621
00:29:51.456 --> 00:29:53.292
No. No. it's not working.

622
00:29:53.375 --> 00:29:55.961
Snake POV. the right way. Take 2.

623
00:29:56.795 --> 00:29:59.506
Sometimes he goes from above in the trees.

624
00:29:59.589 --> 00:30:01.633
sometimes from below in the water.

625
00:30:01.717 --> 00:30:05.846
The toothpick. it unlocked a couple
of aspects of this character for me.

626
00:30:05.929 --> 00:30:07.055
There's something there.

627
00:30:10.100 --> 00:30:11.560
- Ah!
- Why would I be nervous

628
00:30:11.643 --> 00:30:13.145
about doing a love story with Griff?

629
00:30:13.228 --> 00:30:14.396
You guys used to date.

630
00:30:14.938 --> 00:30:16.106
That was a long time ago.

631
00:30:16.189 --> 00:30:19.234
A little bit of chaos
is part of the ingredients.

632
00:30:19.901 --> 00:30:21.111
[grunts. groans]

633
00:30:25.699 --> 00:30:26.908
[shrieks]

634
00:30:26.992 --> 00:30:28.011
[Doug] <i>Maybe look at each other.</i>

635
00:30:28.035 --> 00:30:30.037
This might be the last time
you look at each other.

636
00:30:30.120 --> 00:30:31.921
You'd think you'd be
a little nicer to the guy

637
00:30:31.955 --> 00:30:33.957
who's out here to save your life.

638
00:30:34.041 --> 00:30:35.292
You're an ♪♪♪♪♪♪♪.

639
00:30:35.834 --> 00:30:37.419
[laughs]

640
00:30:37.502 --> 00:30:38.503
Yeah.

641
00:30:39.338 --> 00:30:40.839
And a PhD.

642
00:30:44.551 --> 00:30:45.927
And cut.

643
00:30:46.011 --> 00:30:48.889
- Great stuff. guys. We got it.
- Whoo-hoo!

644
00:30:48.972 --> 00:30:51.641
Should we go one more time?
You wanna try it again?

645
00:30:51.725 --> 00:30:53.060
No. I'm good if you're good.

646
00:30:53.143 --> 00:30:54.895
Let's go one more time.

647
00:31:00.108 --> 00:31:02.736
[gentle music playing]

648
00:31:02.819 --> 00:31:06.740
- The chemistry between you two is…
- Yeah?

649
00:31:06.823 --> 00:31:09.034
- Like we were right back in high school.
- [chuckles]

650
00:31:09.117 --> 00:31:10.452
When you looked up at her…

651
00:31:10.535 --> 00:31:12.037
Well. that's 'cause of your note.

652
00:31:12.120 --> 00:31:13.997
About taking the beat
right before you did it?

653
00:31:14.081 --> 00:31:15.749
Yeah. yeah. It made the scene.

654
00:31:16.541 --> 00:31:17.709
I tell you… [sighs]

655
00:31:18.460 --> 00:31:20.629
I… I never felt like this on <i>S.W.A.T.</i>

656
00:31:20.712 --> 00:31:22.923
I mean. granted
I was only in a couple of episodes.

657
00:31:23.006 --> 00:31:24.966
but it was never collaborative.
It was never fun.

658
00:31:25.050 --> 00:31:26.134
Not… [scoffs]

659
00:31:26.218 --> 00:31:27.803
Not like this. This…

660
00:31:27.886 --> 00:31:30.222
- This is...
- Like we were back on <i>Quatch?</i>

661
00:31:32.265 --> 00:31:33.266
Yeah.

662
00:31:34.810 --> 00:31:35.811
Yeah.

663
00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:43.819
[Doug] Do you guys have chupacabra?

664
00:31:45.237 --> 00:31:46.905
[Claire] Ooh. That looks so good.

665
00:31:47.614 --> 00:31:48.740
Mm-mmm.

666
00:31:48.824 --> 00:31:51.410
Hey. so. one script thing.

667
00:31:51.493 --> 00:31:53.954
I was thinking. at the…
at the midway point.

668
00:31:54.037 --> 00:31:57.874
instead of. uh.
talking the bad guy out of it.

669
00:31:57.958 --> 00:31:58.959
what if…

670
00:31:59.501 --> 00:32:00.919
Claire's character…

671
00:32:02.421 --> 00:32:03.463
Headbutts him?

672
00:32:04.005 --> 00:32:05.757
Sorry. Headbutts him?

673
00:32:06.425 --> 00:32:07.467
Headbutts him.

674
00:32:07.551 --> 00:32:09.428
Or… or…

675
00:32:10.846 --> 00:32:11.847
We both do.

676
00:32:11.930 --> 00:32:13.348
- Double headbutt.
- [Claire scoffs]

677
00:32:13.432 --> 00:32:15.660
- Come on. It's kinda revolutionary.
- [Kenny] Double headbutt.

678
00:32:15.684 --> 00:32:17.102
That is super revolutionary.

679
00:32:17.185 --> 00:32:19.146
Why is that super revolutionary?

680
00:32:19.229 --> 00:32:21.314
Well. it's never been done.

681
00:32:21.398 --> 00:32:24.693
Jesus Christ. This is a beautiful scene
with real stakes. Doug.

682
00:32:24.776 --> 00:32:26.236
Feel free to weigh in here.

683
00:32:26.319 --> 00:32:27.696
Nah. I hear you. I do.

684
00:32:27.779 --> 00:32:30.365
And. as always.
I trust your instincts on this.

685
00:32:32.200 --> 00:32:34.744
But a double headbutt
is pretty revolutionary.

686
00:32:34.828 --> 00:32:37.414
Right? It is…
It's very revolutionary. Yes.

687
00:32:37.497 --> 00:32:39.332
- There's no denying it.
- [Kenny] None!

688
00:32:39.416 --> 00:32:42.461
Oh. come on. Claire. Is the problem that
you don't know how to headbutt?

689
00:32:42.544 --> 00:32:44.588
Why would I not know how to headbutt?

690
00:32:44.671 --> 00:32:47.150
[Griff] We're not born with these skills.
We learn them along the way.

691
00:32:47.174 --> 00:32:50.510
Let me show you.
Tight core. breathe in. hold that breath.

692
00:32:50.594 --> 00:32:51.887
- [Claire] Yeah?
- Hi-yah!

693
00:32:51.970 --> 00:32:53.430
- [Griff] And you can vocalize.
- Wow.

694
00:32:54.139 --> 00:32:58.685
Another kind of headbutt
is more unleashed. just full-on…

695
00:32:58.768 --> 00:33:00.145
[exclaims] Whoo!

696
00:33:00.228 --> 00:33:01.855
He got the arms in there. That's good.

697
00:33:01.938 --> 00:33:03.482
Send that shit into the goal.

698
00:33:03.565 --> 00:33:06.526
Or you put some Brazilian sauce on that.
You know?

699
00:33:07.027 --> 00:33:08.778
- And you go. boom! <i>Toma!</i>
- Oh!

700
00:33:08.862 --> 00:33:10.238
- [Santiago] <i>Toma!</i>
<i>- Toma?</i>

701
00:33:10.322 --> 00:33:11.448
Hey. I love it.

702
00:33:11.531 --> 00:33:12.741
Yeah. that's right.

703
00:33:12.824 --> 00:33:14.993
- Brazilian spice.
- Yeah!

704
00:33:15.076 --> 00:33:18.038
If I was gonna headbutt.
I would go for the bridge of the nose.

705
00:33:18.121 --> 00:33:20.248
- Yes.
- Just crack it. Hi-yah!

706
00:33:20.332 --> 00:33:23.084
- Jesus!
- Yes! That's it.

707
00:33:23.168 --> 00:33:25.045
[overlapping dialogues]

708
00:33:25.128 --> 00:33:27.547
- [Kenny] Jeez. Yeah. that's great.
- And you go. <i>"Toma! Toma!"</i>

709
00:33:27.631 --> 00:33:28.924
[exclaiming]

710
00:33:29.007 --> 00:33:30.842
I think it's a different… <i>Toma!</i>

711
00:33:31.510 --> 00:33:33.220
- [Santiago] <i>Toma!</i>
- [Kenny] Yeah. <i>toma!</i>

712
00:33:33.303 --> 00:33:35.889
- [all chattering excitedly]
- [Griff] Goddamn!

713
00:33:36.389 --> 00:33:38.350
[creaking]

714
00:33:45.065 --> 00:33:47.651
[ominous music playing]

715
00:34:14.344 --> 00:34:17.722
[Doug snoring]

716
00:34:18.306 --> 00:34:19.724
[gasps]

717
00:34:19.808 --> 00:34:21.685
[breathing heavily]

718
00:34:21.768 --> 00:34:23.311
[gasps]

719
00:34:23.395 --> 00:34:25.063
[screams]

720
00:34:27.399 --> 00:34:30.193
I… I'm sorry.
but how could this happen. huh?

721
00:34:30.277 --> 00:34:32.070
Kenny. I thought you said
this guy was a pro.

722
00:34:32.153 --> 00:34:35.574
That's what he said. but he hasn't
provided us with a certificate.

723
00:34:35.657 --> 00:34:37.993
You fixed the crate. right?
It's taken care of?

724
00:34:38.076 --> 00:34:41.413
My thing. My job. Under control. All good.

725
00:34:42.455 --> 00:34:46.626
My Heitor. he's a beautiful. intelligent.
smart. sexy creature.

726
00:34:47.544 --> 00:34:49.713
He does exactly what I command.

727
00:34:50.505 --> 00:34:53.592
And I would never let anything happen

728
00:34:53.675 --> 00:34:58.513
to you or the crazy one.
or her. or her. or this "actor" here.

729
00:34:58.597 --> 00:35:00.807
- What the f…
- So have a good night.

730
00:35:02.684 --> 00:35:07.814
May the sounds of the forest
be the music of your dreams.

731
00:35:10.442 --> 00:35:11.943
Jesus…

732
00:35:12.027 --> 00:35:13.653
Man. he's a poet.

733
00:35:15.280 --> 00:35:17.657
[tense pensive music playing]

734
00:35:27.626 --> 00:35:29.961
Okay. Actors. on your marks.

735
00:35:30.754 --> 00:35:32.255
Santiago. is Heitor ready?

736
00:35:32.339 --> 00:35:34.007
Yes. Heitor is always ready.

737
00:35:34.090 --> 00:35:36.468
Heitor is ready. and action!

738
00:35:41.556 --> 00:35:42.557
[whimpers] Cut. please.

739
00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:46.936
- Um. cut? All right. cut. Yeah.
- Yeah. I just… Sorry. I need a little…

740
00:35:47.020 --> 00:35:48.396
Kenny. do you mind if I…

741
00:35:48.480 --> 00:35:50.690
Santiago. take five. Heitor. five.

742
00:35:51.483 --> 00:35:53.360
- Hey. Wow. that thing. it's really…
- Hey.

743
00:35:53.443 --> 00:35:56.404
It's huge when you see it
up close and personal like that.

744
00:35:56.488 --> 00:35:57.947
Majestic creature.

745
00:35:58.031 --> 00:35:59.783
But I just was wondering…

746
00:35:59.866 --> 00:36:01.660
I… I throw myself in front of the snake

747
00:36:01.743 --> 00:36:05.038
to kind of. uh.
protect Claire's character. right?

748
00:36:05.121 --> 00:36:08.083
- Correct.
- Is there any value in. um.

749
00:36:08.166 --> 00:36:09.417
uh. not doing that?

750
00:36:10.210 --> 00:36:11.419
What? No.

751
00:36:11.503 --> 00:36:14.422
- No. no. he sacrifices himself for her.
- Yeah. Of course.

752
00:36:14.506 --> 00:36:16.841
- It caps his arc. It's so important.
- Right. Right.

753
00:36:16.925 --> 00:36:20.053
- And also. dude. it's totally safe.
- Yeah.

754
00:36:20.136 --> 00:36:22.889
- Santiago has Heitor under control.
- Okay.

755
00:36:22.972 --> 00:36:26.059
- You've got nothing to worry about.
- Yeah. yeah. yeah. Yeah. yeah…

756
00:36:26.142 --> 00:36:28.103
- We're good. You're good.
- Yeah. Okay.

757
00:36:28.186 --> 00:36:29.896
- Okay.
- All right. let's do this.

758
00:36:29.979 --> 00:36:31.356
All right. take it from the top.

759
00:36:33.108 --> 00:36:34.150
Back to one.

760
00:36:35.318 --> 00:36:38.446
Santiago. Heitor? Action!

761
00:36:39.531 --> 00:36:40.532
Go!

762
00:36:41.533 --> 00:36:43.993
I'm not leaving! Not without you. Derek.

763
00:36:44.077 --> 00:36:47.580
This thing's got me.
The world's depending on you.

764
00:36:47.664 --> 00:36:49.416
I'm depending on you.

765
00:36:49.499 --> 00:36:52.377
Goddamn it! I love you. Derek van Hoyle!

766
00:36:52.460 --> 00:36:55.213
It's just… I can't… [groans]

767
00:36:55.296 --> 00:36:58.425
- Put your face right up next to the snake.
- I don't like this.

768
00:36:58.508 --> 00:37:00.820
- I don't want to do it anymore.
- [Doug] Get a tiny bit closer.

769
00:37:00.844 --> 00:37:02.595
Get closer. He's friendly.

770
00:37:02.679 --> 00:37:05.432
- I think you got it. dude!
- [Doug] No. I don't quite have it!

771
00:37:05.515 --> 00:37:08.035
- Doug. you got the shot! You got the shot!
- Hold it! Just a couple more beats.

772
00:37:08.059 --> 00:37:10.311
This is gold.
Just give me one more second.

773
00:37:10.395 --> 00:37:12.522
One inch closer to your face.

774
00:37:12.605 --> 00:37:14.607
- Get it right up in there!
- [hissing]

775
00:37:14.691 --> 00:37:17.569
- You're a hero! No!
- [exclaims]

776
00:37:17.652 --> 00:37:19.487
- [splashing]
- No!

777
00:37:24.617 --> 00:37:28.246
[inaudible sobbing]

778
00:37:29.539 --> 00:37:32.250
[somber music playing]

779
00:37:38.590 --> 00:37:41.968
[slowed down] Oh. shit.

780
00:37:46.181 --> 00:37:48.850
I know you think this is strange.

781
00:37:50.643 --> 00:37:53.980
A grown man getting emotional
over some dead snake.

782
00:37:54.481 --> 00:37:55.565
[whimpers] Jesus.

783
00:37:56.107 --> 00:37:57.400
But I loved him.

784
00:37:58.151 --> 00:38:01.154
and he loved me back.
whatever way he could.

785
00:38:02.280 --> 00:38:04.449
[groaning]

786
00:38:04.532 --> 00:38:07.243
God. No!

787
00:38:07.327 --> 00:38:08.536
[Kenny crying]

788
00:38:08.620 --> 00:38:09.996
Why is Kenny crying?

789
00:38:11.623 --> 00:38:12.623
[kissing]

790
00:38:12.665 --> 00:38:16.419
- Ugh!
- Hey. I don't want you here. Not for this!

791
00:38:16.503 --> 00:38:18.046
He tried to murder me.

792
00:38:18.129 --> 00:38:19.130
- Griff?
- What?

793
00:38:19.214 --> 00:38:21.883
- Let the man grieve.
- You murdered my friend.

794
00:38:21.966 --> 00:38:23.259
Just get out of my face.

795
00:38:23.343 --> 00:38:26.304
- What… Where am I supposed to go?
- Griff! Go! Just move!

796
00:38:26.387 --> 00:38:27.388
Fine!

797
00:38:30.850 --> 00:38:34.813
[somber music playing]

798
00:38:48.660 --> 00:38:53.748
♪ <i>Go in peace. my friend </i> ♪

799
00:38:56.125 --> 00:39:01.548
♪ <i>May the divine snakes welcome you </i> ♪

800
00:39:01.631 --> 00:39:04.968
♪ <i>My dear friend </i> ♪

801
00:39:05.844 --> 00:39:09.347
<i>- ♪ Snakedy snake ♪
- ♪ Snakedy snake. yeah ♪</i>

802
00:39:09.430 --> 00:39:12.892
♪ <i>Snakedy snake </i> ♪

803
00:39:12.976 --> 00:39:16.771
♪ <i>May the divine snakes </i> ♪

804
00:39:16.855 --> 00:39:21.401
♪ <i>Welcome you. welcome you… </i> ♪

805
00:39:22.026 --> 00:39:23.570
[in Portuguese] What do you see?

806
00:39:24.737 --> 00:39:27.699
They're doing
some sort of weird snake funeral.

807
00:39:28.491 --> 00:39:30.535
Snake funeral?

808
00:39:31.286 --> 00:39:33.204
- [loud thump]
- [water sloshing]

809
00:39:36.624 --> 00:39:40.295
[faint singing]

810
00:39:53.850 --> 00:39:54.767
[radio static crackles]

811
00:39:54.851 --> 00:39:58.062
Sorry. I thought I heard something.

812
00:40:01.941 --> 00:40:04.861
[breathing heavily]

813
00:40:15.955 --> 00:40:17.582
[singing continues]

814
00:40:17.665 --> 00:40:19.709
[man screams]

815
00:40:19.792 --> 00:40:20.835
[man] <i>Timo?</i>

816
00:40:22.879 --> 00:40:23.963
<i>Timo!</i>

817
00:40:26.341 --> 00:40:30.219
["End of the Road" by Boyz II Men
playing in video]

818
00:40:37.894 --> 00:40:40.813
- No. Not you. No. Just...
- I know. I'm sorry… I don't mean…

819
00:40:40.897 --> 00:40:43.337
- I'm not trying to disturb you. I just...
- Just leave me alone.

820
00:40:43.399 --> 00:40:44.919
- I'm sorry for your loss.
- [music stops]

821
00:40:44.943 --> 00:40:47.779
I know you don't believe me.
but it's true. I really am.

822
00:40:48.363 --> 00:40:52.116
A friend of mine died once too.
and it hurts.

823
00:40:54.035 --> 00:40:55.036
Was it a snake?

824
00:40:55.620 --> 00:40:56.871
Was it a snake?

825
00:40:58.373 --> 00:40:59.582
No.

826
00:40:59.666 --> 00:41:03.044
It was just a… human person.

827
00:41:03.628 --> 00:41:04.754
Oh.

828
00:41:04.837 --> 00:41:06.339
Yeah. still sad. right?

829
00:41:07.715 --> 00:41:10.885
Totally.
Anyway. I just wanted to say I'm sorry.

830
00:41:12.053 --> 00:41:13.053
Beer?

831
00:41:13.805 --> 00:41:17.725
Well. I have my pills here. but. yeah.
Let's mix it up.

832
00:41:17.809 --> 00:41:22.313
A few commercials. TV.
Did a few episodes of <i>S.W.A.T.</i>

833
00:41:22.855 --> 00:41:24.440
- Oh!<i> S.W.A.T.?</i>
- Yeah.

834
00:41:24.524 --> 00:41:25.817
Oh. I like that one.

835
00:41:25.900 --> 00:41:29.946
I swear. I even had the last line...
Thanks.

836
00:41:30.029 --> 00:41:31.364
The last... Thanks.

837
00:41:31.447 --> 00:41:33.825
- Last line of season three.
- So. what happened?

838
00:41:33.908 --> 00:41:36.911
Well. the producers decided that
they didn't really need that character.

839
00:41:36.995 --> 00:41:38.496
so they got rid of me.

840
00:41:39.622 --> 00:41:43.042
I mean. it's only been going
about eight or nine more seasons.

841
00:41:44.502 --> 00:41:46.295
- They don't deserve you.
- [scoffs]

842
00:41:46.379 --> 00:41:47.672
Yeah. you're a star.

843
00:41:50.049 --> 00:41:52.552
- Thank you.
- Yeah. You've been in movies?

844
00:41:53.136 --> 00:41:56.055
- I'm in an industrial…
- You know what movie I like?

845
00:41:56.139 --> 00:41:58.975
- What?
<i>- The Legend of Bagger Vance.</i>

846
00:41:59.058 --> 00:42:01.519
- [exhales]
- You should do a movie like that.

847
00:42:01.602 --> 00:42:03.062
Man. I wish.

848
00:42:03.146 --> 00:42:04.146
Yeah.

849
00:42:05.606 --> 00:42:08.109
- I like you.
- I like you too.

850
00:42:08.192 --> 00:42:09.402
- You know what?
- What?

851
00:42:09.485 --> 00:42:12.572
I'll get a new snake for your movie now.

852
00:42:12.655 --> 00:42:13.823
- Really?
- Yes.

853
00:42:13.906 --> 00:42:15.908
Oh. my God. Thank you so much.

854
00:42:15.992 --> 00:42:18.077
Yeah. You come with me. of course.

855
00:42:19.579 --> 00:42:20.579
What?

856
00:42:22.749 --> 00:42:25.752
[Griff] Should we be in here?
Maybe we should head back.

857
00:42:30.465 --> 00:42:33.301
- [water sloshes]
- What was that? What was that?

858
00:42:33.384 --> 00:42:35.344
[shushing]

859
00:42:36.471 --> 00:42:37.471
Listen.

860
00:42:38.431 --> 00:42:39.766
There are snakes around here.

861
00:42:40.266 --> 00:42:41.392
I can feel it.

862
00:42:42.643 --> 00:42:43.884
[Griff] What does it feel like?

863
00:42:44.729 --> 00:42:47.523
I don't know. It's just very snaky.

864
00:42:47.607 --> 00:42:49.650
What's… It's snaky?

865
00:42:51.944 --> 00:42:53.196
Ah.

866
00:42:57.200 --> 00:43:00.495
They hear from vibrations on the ground.

867
00:43:02.622 --> 00:43:04.999
Every step we take.

868
00:43:05.666 --> 00:43:07.960
drawing them closer.

869
00:43:09.295 --> 00:43:11.672
And when the jungle goes quiet…

870
00:43:15.218 --> 00:43:17.220
That's when you know they're close.

871
00:43:24.977 --> 00:43:26.104
[Santiago] Yeah.

872
00:43:29.398 --> 00:43:31.984
[tense music playing]

873
00:43:34.278 --> 00:43:36.989
Hey. maybe we should
go back to the boat. huh?

874
00:43:37.073 --> 00:43:40.074
Think it'd be a good idea to go back
to the boat. Let's go back to the boat.

875
00:43:41.285 --> 00:43:42.495
[whispering] Santiago.

876
00:43:43.287 --> 00:43:44.330
Santiago.

877
00:43:45.456 --> 00:43:46.833
[shouting] Santiago!

878
00:43:48.918 --> 00:43:50.419
[animal squawking]

879
00:43:51.045 --> 00:43:52.046
Nope.

880
00:43:52.130 --> 00:43:55.091
[gasping. panting]

881
00:44:04.976 --> 00:44:07.770
[ominous music playing]

882
00:44:15.069 --> 00:44:16.571
Where are you?

883
00:44:18.239 --> 00:44:21.951
[screaming]

884
00:44:34.213 --> 00:44:36.966
Hey. Have you seen Santiago?
I don't think he's come back.

885
00:44:37.049 --> 00:44:41.053
- Back? From what?
- We went out to go get a new snake. We...

886
00:44:41.137 --> 00:44:43.389
You went to find a snake
in the middle of the night?

887
00:44:43.472 --> 00:44:46.034
Yeah. well. we need one for the movie.
It was dark. We got separated.

888
00:44:46.058 --> 00:44:47.143
It was crazy out there.

889
00:44:47.226 --> 00:44:48.704
- [Doug] Griff. Griff. Griff. Griff.
- What?

890
00:44:48.728 --> 00:44:51.814
You went out in the middle of the night
to find a juicy snake in the jungle?

891
00:44:51.898 --> 00:44:53.357
You know what that's called?

892
00:44:54.567 --> 00:44:55.568
Producing.

893
00:44:56.569 --> 00:44:59.071
- Really?
- I guarantee he will be back

894
00:44:59.155 --> 00:45:03.534
with a giant snake.
and you and I are making movies.

895
00:45:03.618 --> 00:45:06.495
You're right. Santiago's a pro.
He'll be fine.

896
00:45:06.579 --> 00:45:08.339
If he's not back soon.
we'll go look for him.

897
00:45:08.915 --> 00:45:12.126
[stereo playing Brazilian music]

898
00:45:16.422 --> 00:45:17.757
[music stops]

899
00:45:31.687 --> 00:45:34.398
Thank you very much. Santiago.

900
00:45:37.902 --> 00:45:40.196
Guys. it's been over an hour.
I have to go find him.

901
00:45:40.821 --> 00:45:41.924
Well. you're not going alone.

902
00:45:41.948 --> 00:45:44.308
Yeah. we're definitely coming with you.
It's safer that way.

903
00:45:44.617 --> 00:45:46.452
[Kenny] Have you guys tried this thing?

904
00:45:46.994 --> 00:45:50.831
It's like a warm bowl of soup
but. [laughs]

905
00:45:50.915 --> 00:45:52.541
but in chair form.

906
00:45:53.376 --> 00:45:54.794
Yeah. man. Chairs.

907
00:45:55.670 --> 00:45:57.213
They. like. hold you. man.

908
00:45:58.172 --> 00:46:00.299
They literally have arms. right?

909
00:46:02.009 --> 00:46:03.552
[chuckles] Oh. wow.

910
00:46:04.387 --> 00:46:06.180
Like when your parents are gone…

911
00:46:09.392 --> 00:46:11.143
We still have chairs. you know?

912
00:46:13.187 --> 00:46:15.272
The hell are you talking about?

913
00:46:15.356 --> 00:46:17.191
Let's go find Santiago.

914
00:46:17.274 --> 00:46:19.151
Let's get a snake for our snake movie.

915
00:46:19.235 --> 00:46:21.320
Yeah. Santiago! Let's go!

916
00:46:22.196 --> 00:46:24.740
[animals chittering]

917
00:46:24.824 --> 00:46:27.284
[tense music playing]

918
00:46:28.828 --> 00:46:32.373
[whispering]
Hey. what direction are we headed in?

919
00:46:32.456 --> 00:46:33.666
Um…

920
00:46:34.542 --> 00:46:36.127
[whispering] Like. that way.

921
00:46:36.210 --> 00:46:38.838
Wait. Kenny. are you high right now?

922
00:46:38.921 --> 00:46:40.965
Yeah. but I'm good. I already peaked.

923
00:46:41.048 --> 00:46:42.341
Jesus Christ. Kenny.

924
00:46:42.425 --> 00:46:43.926
We're completely lost.

925
00:46:46.512 --> 00:46:48.639
Wait. You guys. this way.

926
00:46:49.432 --> 00:46:51.225
[Doug] It looks like an old camper van.

927
00:46:51.851 --> 00:46:55.479
[tense music playing]

928
00:47:08.075 --> 00:47:10.303
- [walkie-talkie bleeps]
- [in Portuguese] Ana is not on the boat.

929
00:47:10.327 --> 00:47:13.039
I need you to search the area.

930
00:47:13.122 --> 00:47:16.208
The men are scared
to go deeper into the jungle.

931
00:47:16.292 --> 00:47:18.461
<i>I don't care. we have to find her.</i>

932
00:47:23.549 --> 00:47:24.717
[Griff] What is that?

933
00:47:24.800 --> 00:47:27.511
[Kenny chuckles] Oh.
maybe Santiago's sleeping in there.

934
00:47:27.595 --> 00:47:28.596
[Doug] <i>Hola.</i>

935
00:47:28.679 --> 00:47:31.057
[animals chittering]

936
00:47:31.140 --> 00:47:32.349
[Doug] Whoa.

937
00:47:33.350 --> 00:47:36.312
Looks totally abandoned. Anybody home?

938
00:47:37.146 --> 00:47:38.439
[Claire sighs]

939
00:47:42.443 --> 00:47:43.986
Maybe some food and water.

940
00:47:44.070 --> 00:47:45.446
Yeah. We could stay here.

941
00:47:45.529 --> 00:47:46.655
At least tonight.

942
00:47:51.952 --> 00:47:55.164
Oh. man. there's gotta be snacks in here.

943
00:47:56.290 --> 00:47:57.875
[rustling nearby]

944
00:47:57.958 --> 00:47:59.376
[shushes]

945
00:48:03.506 --> 00:48:05.591
[rustling]

946
00:48:06.926 --> 00:48:10.429
[tense music playing]

947
00:48:16.268 --> 00:48:18.145
[Ana breathes shakily]

948
00:48:18.229 --> 00:48:20.189
[all breathing shakily]

949
00:48:23.359 --> 00:48:25.277
- [all scream]
- Oh. my God.

950
00:48:25.361 --> 00:48:26.588
- [Kenny] Oh. God.
- [Doug] Santiago!

951
00:48:26.612 --> 00:48:27.696
[Claire] Oh. God.

952
00:48:27.780 --> 00:48:29.365
- [Doug gasps]
- [Kenny] Dang!

953
00:48:30.366 --> 00:48:31.951
That's where that guy went!

954
00:48:32.034 --> 00:48:33.869
Oh. my God. What is out there?

955
00:48:35.996 --> 00:48:38.499
[low growling]

956
00:48:43.420 --> 00:48:44.880
[Claire breathes shakily]

957
00:48:44.964 --> 00:48:46.841
- [Ana] We gotta go now!
- Okay. Go. go. go.

958
00:48:46.924 --> 00:48:48.318
- Let's get out of here.
- [Ana] Let's go. let's go.

959
00:48:48.342 --> 00:48:50.928
- We can't let it crush the van.
- Crush the van?

960
00:48:51.011 --> 00:48:52.030
- It's not working.
- [engine sputtering]

961
00:48:52.054 --> 00:48:53.139
- What?
- It's not…

962
00:48:53.222 --> 00:48:55.516
- Damn it!
- It's a camper van. probably!

963
00:48:55.599 --> 00:48:57.726
It's got a split… [stutters]
A split-charge battery.

964
00:48:57.810 --> 00:49:00.187
The relay probably popped off.
It's underneath the hood.

965
00:49:00.271 --> 00:49:01.605
Kenny. can you fix it?

966
00:49:01.689 --> 00:49:03.983
Usually I could fix it. yes.
but I'm having…

967
00:49:04.066 --> 00:49:07.194
I'm still having some visual problems
because of the… [chuckles]

968
00:49:07.278 --> 00:49:08.696
You did it to me again.

969
00:49:08.779 --> 00:49:13.409
You did it on the wedding video
and now you're wasted off your ass. again.

970
00:49:13.492 --> 00:49:14.952
I'm really sorry. boss.

971
00:49:15.035 --> 00:49:18.706
[groans] Buffalo sober.
You're Buffalo sober.

972
00:49:18.789 --> 00:49:19.790
Do you have any more?

973
00:49:19.874 --> 00:49:22.001
Griff. please can you fix it?

974
00:49:22.084 --> 00:49:23.645
[whispering] I think I'm better suited
to be our wheel man.

975
00:49:23.669 --> 00:49:25.939
What are you talking about?
I've always been a better driver than you.

976
00:49:25.963 --> 00:49:27.204
No. you've been a safer driver.

977
00:49:27.256 --> 00:49:29.341
I passed the driver's test
on my first try.

978
00:49:29.425 --> 00:49:30.759
You took three times.

979
00:49:30.843 --> 00:49:32.261
Yeah. but that was 'cause of yield.

980
00:49:32.344 --> 00:49:34.054
I didn't know… Now I know what that is.

981
00:49:34.138 --> 00:49:36.348
[normal volume] Oh. my God.
We're gonna die.

982
00:49:36.891 --> 00:49:38.434
[breathes heavily]

983
00:49:38.517 --> 00:49:39.560
Sorry.

984
00:49:41.353 --> 00:49:42.396
I'll just fix it.

985
00:49:44.565 --> 00:49:48.068
[tense music playing]

986
00:50:08.964 --> 00:50:10.549
[hood clicks open]

987
00:50:17.806 --> 00:50:19.475
[hood creaking]

988
00:50:28.192 --> 00:50:29.652
[creaks]

989
00:50:50.339 --> 00:50:52.132
[hood thuds. clatters]

990
00:50:52.925 --> 00:50:54.218
[Claire breathes shakily]

991
00:50:54.301 --> 00:50:57.930
- [engine starts]
- [low growling]

992
00:50:58.013 --> 00:50:59.014
[screams]

993
00:50:59.098 --> 00:51:00.474
- Doug!
- Go. go. go!

994
00:51:01.267 --> 00:51:03.185
Let me get up. Hey. wait! Stop! Stop!

995
00:51:03.269 --> 00:51:05.729
Griff. where are you going?
Don't leave without me!

996
00:51:05.813 --> 00:51:07.064
[grunts]

997
00:51:08.857 --> 00:51:10.025
Oh. shit!

998
00:51:11.068 --> 00:51:12.778
[groans. cries]

999
00:51:12.861 --> 00:51:13.988
[Griff] You saw it. right?

1000
00:51:14.071 --> 00:51:15.799
What was that?
They're not supposed to get that big.

1001
00:51:15.823 --> 00:51:18.075
Oh. God. It was like a dinosaur.

1002
00:51:18.158 --> 00:51:19.535
[screams]

1003
00:51:19.618 --> 00:51:22.121
[engines revving]

1004
00:51:22.955 --> 00:51:23.956
Hey!

1005
00:51:26.792 --> 00:51:28.669
Hey. maybe we can ask these guys for help.

1006
00:51:28.752 --> 00:51:29.586
- Hey!
- [Claire] Hey!

1007
00:51:29.670 --> 00:51:31.922
- We have to stop.
- Do not stop the car.

1008
00:51:32.006 --> 00:51:33.299
Ana. what is going on?

1009
00:51:33.382 --> 00:51:36.260
They're illegal gold miners
who patrol the jungles around here.

1010
00:51:36.343 --> 00:51:37.720
These guys are dangerous.

1011
00:51:37.803 --> 00:51:40.639
They'll kill anyone
who crosses into their territory.

1012
00:51:40.723 --> 00:51:43.642
- Oh. shit. They're trying to kill us.
- [Griff] F♪♪♪!

1013
00:51:43.726 --> 00:51:45.227
[Doug] Why are they shooting at us?

1014
00:51:45.311 --> 00:51:46.854
- [gunshot]
- [Griff exclaims]

1015
00:51:46.937 --> 00:51:48.772
[Claire]
Griff. can't you drive any faster?

1016
00:51:49.523 --> 00:51:53.444
- Whoa!
- Whoa. whoa. Ana. what are you doing?

1017
00:51:53.527 --> 00:51:55.029
- [Ana grunts]
- Whoa!

1018
00:51:55.112 --> 00:51:56.196
[Ana grunting]

1019
00:51:57.448 --> 00:51:59.950
- [Doug] Kenny. are you getting this?
- [Kenny] Yes!

1020
00:52:01.285 --> 00:52:02.619
Keep rolling!

1021
00:52:04.371 --> 00:52:05.664
[Ana groans]

1022
00:52:05.748 --> 00:52:08.000
Griff. faster.

1023
00:52:09.752 --> 00:52:11.170
[man exclaims]

1024
00:52:11.253 --> 00:52:12.629
[Griff] Only one left.

1025
00:52:12.713 --> 00:52:14.173
[groaning]

1026
00:52:15.716 --> 00:52:16.925
[tires squeal]

1027
00:52:17.926 --> 00:52:19.261
[door slides open]

1028
00:52:27.811 --> 00:52:29.521
[breathing heavily]

1029
00:52:36.236 --> 00:52:38.197
- Where is she?
- [gasps] Oh. my God.

1030
00:52:38.280 --> 00:52:39.323
Where is she?

1031
00:52:42.409 --> 00:52:44.078
Who? Who do… Who do you mean?

1032
00:52:44.161 --> 00:52:45.704
I know there's someone else here.

1033
00:52:45.788 --> 00:52:48.957
- So. where is she?
- [Ana exclaims]

1034
00:52:49.041 --> 00:52:50.292
[thuds]

1035
00:52:53.504 --> 00:52:54.505
Let's go. come on.

1036
00:52:55.047 --> 00:52:56.173
We gotta go. Fast.

1037
00:52:56.256 --> 00:52:57.633
[Claire breathing heavily]

1038
00:52:58.217 --> 00:53:00.135
Look. I can get you guys out of here.

1039
00:53:00.219 --> 00:53:02.221
All we need to do is keep heading north.

1040
00:53:02.846 --> 00:53:06.266
There's a small airport
about a day and a half from here.

1041
00:53:06.350 --> 00:53:07.851
You can get us home?

1042
00:53:07.935 --> 00:53:09.561
- [Ana] Yes.
- Get us home.

1043
00:53:09.645 --> 00:53:10.813
I think we gotta call it.

1044
00:53:11.522 --> 00:53:14.108
Man. we've got such good stuff.
and we're so close.

1045
00:53:14.775 --> 00:53:17.820
Really? We're going home?

1046
00:53:17.903 --> 00:53:19.113
[Doug] Buddy. I know.

1047
00:53:19.196 --> 00:53:21.490
I don't wanna go home empty-handed either.

1048
00:53:21.573 --> 00:53:23.826
But we came out here to make <i>Anaconda.</i>

1049
00:53:24.785 --> 00:53:25.994
and now we're in it.

1050
00:53:27.496 --> 00:53:28.414
[mumbles]

1051
00:53:28.497 --> 00:53:30.582
[tapping on table] Yeah.

1052
00:53:34.378 --> 00:53:35.504
I'm sorry.

1053
00:53:41.510 --> 00:53:42.845
[sighs]

1054
00:53:47.307 --> 00:53:48.307
[kisses]

1055
00:53:49.393 --> 00:53:50.978
[exhales deeply]

1056
00:53:51.061 --> 00:53:55.941
[epic music playing]

1057
00:54:12.791 --> 00:54:13.959
[exhales deeply]

1058
00:54:14.543 --> 00:54:17.880
Guys. emergency meeting.

1059
00:54:17.963 --> 00:54:19.882
Cast and crew only. Kenny. sit down.

1060
00:54:19.965 --> 00:54:21.717
- [Kenny] What is that?
- New pages.

1061
00:54:21.800 --> 00:54:23.510
We have some time before the next port

1062
00:54:23.594 --> 00:54:27.890
and I had an idea last night that I think
is just too damn good not to shoot.

1063
00:54:27.973 --> 00:54:30.684
Doug. everybody's pretty burnt. man.

1064
00:54:30.767 --> 00:54:32.936
Just hear me out.
I'm begging you please. Kenny.

1065
00:54:33.020 --> 00:54:34.730
- All right. Sorry. boss.
- [Doug] Thank you.

1066
00:54:34.813 --> 00:54:37.983
What if you two.
on your way to find the anaconda.

1067
00:54:38.066 --> 00:54:41.153
ran into a total badass
on an incredible quest?

1068
00:54:41.236 --> 00:54:43.363
Oh. That's interesting.

1069
00:54:43.447 --> 00:54:46.867
Let me guess.
to expose illegal gold miners?

1070
00:54:46.950 --> 00:54:48.702
- Bingo.
- Raises the stakes.

1071
00:54:48.785 --> 00:54:49.912
[Doug] Exactly.

1072
00:54:49.995 --> 00:54:51.973
And while they're hunting down
this mythical snake.

1073
00:54:51.997 --> 00:54:53.838
they actually end up
fighting the real villain.

1074
00:54:54.374 --> 00:54:55.667
An even bigger snake.

1075
00:54:55.751 --> 00:54:58.212
- Man.
- Oh. yeah. Yes.

1076
00:54:58.712 --> 00:55:00.839
- Man.
- I like this.

1077
00:55:01.381 --> 00:55:02.257
This is good.

1078
00:55:02.341 --> 00:55:05.427
And if we add this element.
it does make the movie much bigger.

1079
00:55:06.136 --> 00:55:08.764
Like. now. it's… about something.

1080
00:55:11.225 --> 00:55:12.351
Themes.

1081
00:55:12.434 --> 00:55:14.061
Themes. [Chuckles]

1082
00:55:14.144 --> 00:55:16.313
Uh…

1083
00:55:19.566 --> 00:55:20.901
Uh-huh.

1084
00:55:20.984 --> 00:55:22.194
Yeah.

1085
00:55:22.277 --> 00:55:23.946
Okay. You know what. guys?

1086
00:55:24.029 --> 00:55:26.865
[spluttering] I… I didn't wanna say
anything before. but…

1087
00:55:28.909 --> 00:55:30.619
This thing might be an Awards play.

1088
00:55:31.453 --> 00:55:35.332
- [Claire gasps]
- I mean. the Academy loves social horror.

1089
00:55:35.415 --> 00:55:36.500
- Right?
- [Griff] Yeah.

1090
00:55:37.918 --> 00:55:41.171
Dude. you could be the White Jordan Peele.

1091
00:55:41.797 --> 00:55:44.299
[sighs] I was thinking the same thing.

1092
00:55:47.636 --> 00:55:49.346
We've been through so much. you guys.

1093
00:55:49.972 --> 00:55:51.682
Let's finish this movie.

1094
00:55:54.101 --> 00:55:55.310
I'm in.

1095
00:55:55.394 --> 00:55:56.728
- Let's do it.
- [Griff] Yeah.

1096
00:55:56.812 --> 00:56:02.025
Oh… Who are you gonna get…
to play this new. awesome character?

1097
00:56:04.319 --> 00:56:05.571
[exclaims in Portuguese]

1098
00:56:05.654 --> 00:56:07.990
[Kenny] Ow! [Groaning]

1099
00:56:08.073 --> 00:56:09.283
[speaking Portuguese]

1100
00:56:09.366 --> 00:56:11.243
And cut. Yes!

1101
00:56:11.326 --> 00:56:12.845
- [Ana] Was it good?
- That's what I'm talking about.

1102
00:56:12.869 --> 00:56:13.704
- [Claire] Nice.
- [Kenny] Yeah.

1103
00:56:13.787 --> 00:56:16.081
- You sure you've never acted before?
- I swear.

1104
00:56:16.164 --> 00:56:17.958
Some of the best acting I've ever seen.

1105
00:56:18.584 --> 00:56:19.751
You're a natural.

1106
00:56:19.835 --> 00:56:21.145
- [Doug] You're incredible.
- [Ana] Thank you.

1107
00:56:21.169 --> 00:56:22.838
Take five. Next up. we got 72.

1108
00:56:23.672 --> 00:56:27.050
- Guys. you see what I'm saying?
- Yeah.

1109
00:56:27.134 --> 00:56:28.719
- She's incredible. right?
- Yeah.

1110
00:56:28.802 --> 00:56:30.637
Hey. uh… a question. though.

1111
00:56:30.721 --> 00:56:35.183
If… if she saves us. it doesn't really
give my character anything to do.

1112
00:56:35.267 --> 00:56:36.310
Yeah.

1113
00:56:36.393 --> 00:56:40.439
This was supposed to be the moment where
my character starts falling for Derek.

1114
00:56:40.522 --> 00:56:44.443
so he needs to do something heroic.
you know? Unselfish.

1115
00:56:44.526 --> 00:56:47.070
I don't know. you guys.
this just feels like her moment.

1116
00:56:47.154 --> 00:56:49.031
she actually did it in real life.

1117
00:56:49.656 --> 00:56:52.326
But good news.
I'm gonna shoot all the rest on her

1118
00:56:52.409 --> 00:56:53.827
so you guys have the day off.

1119
00:56:54.745 --> 00:56:55.829
See you later.

1120
00:56:57.164 --> 00:56:58.457
Take the day off.

1121
00:56:59.916 --> 00:57:01.168
Huh.

1122
00:57:01.251 --> 00:57:03.629
[gentle music playing]

1123
00:57:07.090 --> 00:57:10.719
[Claire] This is our movie. Griff.
and he's just cutting us out.

1124
00:57:10.802 --> 00:57:12.638
[Griff] Yep.
Welcome to show business. baby.

1125
00:57:12.721 --> 00:57:15.974
You're not in it unless you're getting
screwed over by your friends.

1126
00:57:16.058 --> 00:57:17.434
[chuckles]

1127
00:57:17.517 --> 00:57:18.602
Yeah.

1128
00:57:20.520 --> 00:57:24.149
You ever wake up and wonder
what the hell have I done with my life?

1129
00:57:24.691 --> 00:57:27.527
- [chuckling] Oh. yeah. Like. every day.
- Mmm.

1130
00:57:27.611 --> 00:57:30.113
Hey. at least you had the guts
to go after what you wanted.

1131
00:57:30.197 --> 00:57:32.074
- No.
- You think I wanted to go to law school?

1132
00:57:32.574 --> 00:57:34.368
What have I got to show
for it though. huh?

1133
00:57:34.451 --> 00:57:35.452
You know what I have?

1134
00:57:35.535 --> 00:57:39.039
I have a terrible apartment
and a 74-year-old roommate.

1135
00:57:40.332 --> 00:57:44.378
[sighs] Sometimes I go to Trader Joe's
just to feel air conditioning.

1136
00:57:45.879 --> 00:57:47.339
You at least have a career.

1137
00:57:49.091 --> 00:57:50.842
I mean. what do I have to show for it?

1138
00:57:52.302 --> 00:57:55.138
I've got no family. No career.

1139
00:57:56.223 --> 00:57:57.766
Never done anything that matters.

1140
00:57:58.475 --> 00:57:59.601
No nothing.

1141
00:58:00.435 --> 00:58:01.435
[sighs]

1142
00:58:02.020 --> 00:58:03.230
It's never too late.

1143
00:58:11.405 --> 00:58:12.447
[knocking on door]

1144
00:58:12.531 --> 00:58:14.116
[Doug] <i>Griff. I know you're in there.</i>

1145
00:58:14.199 --> 00:58:15.492
<i>Let's make a movie.</i>

1146
00:58:16.910 --> 00:58:19.287
- [Griff groans]
- Ugh.

1147
00:58:19.997 --> 00:58:20.998
<i>Hola. amigo.</i>

1148
00:58:21.081 --> 00:58:23.917
Jesus. Come on. get dressed.
We've got a packed day.

1149
00:58:24.001 --> 00:58:27.462
What are you talking about? I am dressed.
I'm dressed really pretty… very nicely.

1150
00:58:27.546 --> 00:58:29.464
All right.
Can you just take a cold shower?

1151
00:58:29.548 --> 00:58:30.716
We gotta film. like. now.

1152
00:58:30.799 --> 00:58:33.343
Here's an idea. You know what
you should call the movie?

1153
00:58:33.427 --> 00:58:35.637
"Ana-conda." Get it?

1154
00:58:36.138 --> 00:58:38.015
"Ana-conda." 'cause of Ana.

1155
00:58:38.098 --> 00:58:39.808
Can you just get in costume?

1156
00:58:39.891 --> 00:58:42.492
Man. you know what? You wouldn't
even be here if it wasn't for me.

1157
00:58:42.894 --> 00:58:44.688
Without me.
you'd still be stuck in Buffalo

1158
00:58:44.771 --> 00:58:47.399
shooting your bullshit wedding videos.

1159
00:58:47.482 --> 00:58:49.192
[breathes heavily] Films.

1160
00:58:49.276 --> 00:58:50.986
Yeah. you can tell yourself that.

1161
00:58:51.069 --> 00:58:53.864
My God. you know what?
I… I… I vouched for you too.

1162
00:58:53.947 --> 00:58:56.188
Even the rights holders. they're like.
"Who is this guy?"

1163
00:58:56.241 --> 00:58:57.659
I said. "Trust me. He's good."

1164
00:58:58.285 --> 00:58:59.828
[boat approaching]

1165
00:58:59.911 --> 00:59:00.911
What is that?

1166
00:59:04.875 --> 00:59:06.102
[announcer] <i>Attention. all crew.</i>

1167
00:59:06.126 --> 00:59:09.713
<i>Let's get prepped for scene 85.
location Bravo.</i>

1168
00:59:09.796 --> 00:59:11.006
<i>Five minutes.</i>

1169
00:59:11.089 --> 00:59:14.176
- [Claire] Are they making a movie?
- [announcer] <i>Five minutes to arrival.</i>

1170
00:59:14.259 --> 00:59:17.721
Excuse me. are you guys shooting a movie?

1171
00:59:17.804 --> 00:59:19.681
We're doing a reboot of <i>Anaconda.</i>

1172
00:59:20.390 --> 00:59:21.390
[Doug] Come again?

1173
00:59:21.850 --> 00:59:24.770
- [crew member] A reboot of <i>Anaconda.</i>
<i>- Anaconda?</i>

1174
00:59:25.270 --> 00:59:27.439
- Like. Ice Cube <i>Anaconda?</i>
- Yeah.

1175
00:59:27.522 --> 00:59:28.982
Sony is rebooting it.

1176
00:59:29.524 --> 00:59:32.110
I know. No new ideas.

1177
00:59:36.782 --> 00:59:39.076
[tense music playing]

1178
00:59:46.083 --> 00:59:47.167
That's weird.

1179
00:59:49.503 --> 00:59:50.879
So. let me get this straight.

1180
00:59:51.505 --> 00:59:54.049
You don't have the rights to <i>Anaconda?</i>

1181
00:59:55.383 --> 00:59:56.383
No. well. I…

1182
00:59:57.552 --> 00:59:58.595
Not legally.

1183
00:59:59.638 --> 01:00:02.474
[Doug] And you've never owned
the rights to <i>Anaconda?</i>

1184
01:00:05.519 --> 01:00:07.062
I mean. who owns <i>Anaconda?</i>

1185
01:00:07.145 --> 01:00:09.940
Sony. Sony owns <i>Anaconda.</i>

1186
01:00:10.023 --> 01:00:11.125
Yeah. no. no. I know. I know.

1187
01:00:11.149 --> 01:00:14.152
I mean. like. you know. like.
in the larger sense.

1188
01:00:14.236 --> 01:00:16.613
Why would you tell us
that you had the rights

1189
01:00:16.696 --> 01:00:19.199
to the goddamn <i>Anaconda </i>franchise

1190
01:00:19.282 --> 01:00:24.079
when you very much don't have the rights
to the goddamn <i>Anaconda </i>franchise?

1191
01:00:24.162 --> 01:00:26.915
[spluttering]
Do… we really even need the rights?

1192
01:00:26.998 --> 01:00:28.559
Really? I mean. like. who gives a shit?

1193
01:00:30.460 --> 01:00:32.129
- About IP?
- Yeah.

1194
01:00:32.212 --> 01:00:34.047
Literally everyone. [Chuckles]

1195
01:00:34.131 --> 01:00:37.217
That's what big movies are!
That's why we're here!

1196
01:00:37.300 --> 01:00:40.053
- You think that's why we're here?
- Yes. that's why we're here!

1197
01:00:40.137 --> 01:00:41.513
We almost died!

1198
01:00:41.596 --> 01:00:45.475
We're out in the middle
of the goddamn jungle… for a lie!

1199
01:00:45.559 --> 01:00:47.102
I had to lie!

1200
01:00:47.978 --> 01:00:50.098
I had to lie to you!
You wouldn't have come otherwise!

1201
01:00:50.147 --> 01:00:51.815
You wouldn't… None of you would have...

1202
01:00:51.898 --> 01:00:54.734
- [groans] Bullshit!
- [Griff] Not bullshit.

1203
01:00:54.818 --> 01:00:57.130
It's why you never came out
to L.A. with me in the first place.

1204
01:00:57.154 --> 01:01:00.115
even though we had
a whole plan to work together.

1205
01:01:00.198 --> 01:01:03.201
Your whole life. you've just…
it's been dictated by fear.

1206
01:01:05.078 --> 01:01:06.079
Griff.

1207
01:01:07.789 --> 01:01:08.789
you're fired.

1208
01:01:09.457 --> 01:01:11.126
- What?
- You're fired.

1209
01:01:14.171 --> 01:01:15.255
No. No. I'm not.

1210
01:01:15.338 --> 01:01:17.048
You can't fire me. You know why?

1211
01:01:17.799 --> 01:01:19.593
Because I quit already.

1212
01:01:20.552 --> 01:01:21.552
Last night.

1213
01:01:24.890 --> 01:01:26.308
I just didn't tell anybody yet.

